168 NTSTATUS
169 CmDeleteValueKey(
170  IN PCM_KEY_CONTROL_BLOCK KeyControlBlock,
171  IN UNICODE_STRING ValueName // RAW
172  )
173 /*++
174 
175 Routine Description:
176 
177  One of the value entries of a registry key may be removed with this call.
178 
179  The value entry with ValueName matching ValueName is removed from the key.
180  If no such entry exists, an error is returned.
181 
182 Arguments:
183 
184  KeyControlBlock - pointer to kcb for key to operate on
185 
186  ValueName - The name of the value to be deleted. NULL is a legal name.
187 
188 Return Value:
189 
190  NTSTATUS
191 
192 --*/
193 {
194  NTSTATUS status;
195  PCM_KEY_NODE pcell = NULL;
196  PCHILD_LIST plist;
197  PCM_KEY_VALUE Value = NULL;
198  ULONG targetindex;
199  HCELL_INDEX ChildCell;
200  PHHIVE Hive;
201  HCELL_INDEX Cell;
202  LARGE_INTEGER systemtime;
203 
204  CmKdPrintEx((DPFLTR_CONFIG_ID,CML_CM,"CmDeleteValueKey\n"));
205 
206  status = STATUS_OBJECT_NAME_NOT_FOUND;
207 
208  ChildCell = HCELL_NIL;
209 
210  CmpLockRegistry();
211  //
212  // serialize access to this key.
213  //
214  CmpLockKCBExclusive(KeyControlBlock);
215 
216  PERFINFO_REG_DELETE_VALUE(KeyControlBlock, &ValueName);
217 
218  //
219  // no edits, not even this one, on keys marked for deletion
220  //
221  if (KeyControlBlock->Delete) {
222  CmpUnlockKCB(KeyControlBlock);
223  CmpUnlockRegistry();
224 
225  // Mark the hive as read only
226  CmpMarkAllBinsReadOnly(Hive);
227 
228  return STATUS_KEY_DELETED;
229  }
230 
231  Hive = KeyControlBlock->KeyHive;
232  Cell = KeyControlBlock->KeyCell;
233 
234  //
235  // no flush from this point on
236  //
237  CmpLockHiveFlusherShared((PCMHIVE)Hive);
238  try {
239 
240  pcell = (PCM_KEY_NODE)HvGetCell(Hive, Cell);
241  if( pcell == NULL ) {
242  //
243  // we couldn't map a view for the bin containing this cell
244  //
245  status = STATUS_INSUFFICIENT_RESOURCES;
246  leave;
247  }
248 
249  // Mark the hive as read only
250  CmpMarkAllBinsReadOnly(Hive);
251 
252  plist = &(pcell->ValueList);
253 
254  if (plist->Count != 0) {
255 
256  //
257  // The parent has at least one value, map in the list of
258  // values and call CmpFindChildInList
259  //
260 
261  //
262  // plist -> the CHILD_LIST structure
263  // pchild -> the child node structure being examined
264  //
265 
266  if( CmpFindNameInList(Hive,
267  plist,
268  &ValueName,
269  &targetindex,
270  &ChildCell) == FALSE ) {
271 
272  // Mark the hive as read only
273  CmpMarkAllBinsReadOnly(Hive);
274 
275  status = STATUS_INSUFFICIENT_RESOURCES;
276  leave;
277  }
278 
279  if (ChildCell != HCELL_NIL) {
280 
281  //
282  // 1. the desired target was found
283  // 2. ChildCell is it's HCELL_INDEX
284  // 3. targetaddress points to it
285  // 4. targetindex is it's index
286  //
287 
288  //
289  // attempt to mark all relevant cells dirty
290  //
291  if (!(HvMarkCellDirty(Hive, Cell, FALSE) &&
292  HvMarkCellDirty(Hive, pcell->ValueList.List, FALSE) &&
293  HvMarkCellDirty(Hive, ChildCell, FALSE)))
294 
295  {
296  // Mark the hive as read only
297  CmpMarkAllBinsReadOnly(Hive);
298 
299  status = STATUS_NO_LOG_SPACE;
300  leave;
301  }
302 
303  Value = (PCM_KEY_VALUE)HvGetCell(Hive,ChildCell);
304  if( Value == NULL ) {
305  //
306  // could not map view inside
307  // this is impossible as we just dirtied the view
308  //
309  ASSERT( FALSE );
310  // Mark the hive as read only
311  CmpMarkAllBinsReadOnly(Hive);
312 
313  status = STATUS_INSUFFICIENT_RESOURCES;
314  leave;
315  }
316  if( !CmpMarkValueDataDirty(Hive,Value) ) {
317  // Mark the hive as read only
318  CmpMarkAllBinsReadOnly(Hive);
319 
320  status = STATUS_NO_LOG_SPACE;
321  leave;
322  }
323 
324  // sanity
325  ASSERT_CELL_DIRTY(Hive,pcell->ValueList.List);
326  ASSERT_CELL_DIRTY(Hive,ChildCell);
327 
328  if( !NT_SUCCESS(CmpRemoveValueFromList(Hive,targetindex,plist)) ) {
329  //
330  // bail out !
331  //
332  status = STATUS_INSUFFICIENT_RESOURCES;
333  leave;
334  }
335  if( CmpFreeValue(Hive, ChildCell) == FALSE ) {
336  //
337  // we couldn't map a view inside above call
338  //
339  status = STATUS_INSUFFICIENT_RESOURCES;
340  leave;
341  }
342 
343  KeQuerySystemTime(&systemtime);
344  pcell->LastWriteTime = systemtime;
345  // cache it in the kcb too.
346  KeyControlBlock->KcbLastWriteTime = systemtime;
347 
348  // some sanity asserts
349  ASSERT( pcell->MaxValueNameLen == KeyControlBlock->KcbMaxValueNameLen );
350  ASSERT( pcell->MaxValueDataLen == KeyControlBlock->KcbMaxValueDataLen );
351  ASSERT_CELL_DIRTY(Hive,Cell);
352 
353  if (pcell->ValueList.Count == 0) {
354  pcell->MaxValueNameLen = 0;
355  pcell->MaxValueDataLen = 0;
356  // update the kcb cache too
357  KeyControlBlock->KcbMaxValueNameLen = 0;
358  KeyControlBlock->KcbMaxValueDataLen = 0;
359  }
360 
361  //
362  // Invalidate and rebuild the cache
363  //
364  CmpCleanUpKcbValueCache(KeyControlBlock);
365  CmpSetUpKcbValueCache(KeyControlBlock,plist->Count,plist->List);
366 
367  CmpReportNotify(
368  KeyControlBlock,
369  KeyControlBlock->KeyHive,
370  KeyControlBlock->KeyCell,
371  REG_NOTIFY_CHANGE_LAST_SET
372  );
373  status = STATUS_SUCCESS;
374  } else {
375  status = STATUS_OBJECT_NAME_NOT_FOUND;
376  }
377  }
378  } finally {
379  if(pcell != NULL){
380  HvReleaseCell(Hive, Cell);
381  }
382  if(Value != NULL){
383  ASSERT( ChildCell != HCELL_NIL );
384  HvReleaseCell(Hive, ChildCell);
385  }
386 
387  CmpUnlockHiveFlusher((PCMHIVE)Hive);
388  CmpUnlockKCB(KeyControlBlock);
389  CmpUnlockRegistry();
390  }
391 
392  // Mark the hive as read only
393  CmpMarkAllBinsReadOnly(Hive);
394 
395  return status;
396 }

399 NTSTATUS
400 CmEnumerateKey(
401  IN PCM_KEY_CONTROL_BLOCK KeyControlBlock,
402  IN ULONG Index,
403  IN KEY_INFORMATION_CLASS KeyInformationClass,
404  IN PVOID KeyInformation,
405  IN ULONG Length,
406  IN PULONG ResultLength
407  )
408 /*++
409 
410 Routine Description:
411 
412  Enumerate sub keys, return data on Index'th entry.
413 
414  CmEnumerateKey returns the name of the Index'th sub key of the open
415  key specified. The value STATUS_NO_MORE_ENTRIES will be
416  returned if value of Index is larger than the number of sub keys.
417 
418  Note that Index is simply a way to select among child keys. Two calls
419  to CmEnumerateKey with the same Index are NOT guaranteed to return
420  the same results.
421 
422  If KeyInformation is not long enough to hold all requested data,
423  STATUS_BUFFER_OVERFLOW will be returned, and ResultLength will be
424  set to the number of bytes actually required.
425 
426 Arguments:
427 
428  KeyControlBlock - pointer to the KCB that describes the key
429 
430  Index - Specifies the (0-based) number of the sub key to be returned.
431 
432  KeyInformationClass - Specifies the type of information returned in
433  Buffer. One of the following types:
434 
435  KeyBasicInformation - return last write time, title index, and name.
436  (see KEY_BASIC_INFORMATION structure)
437 
438  KeyNodeInformation - return last write time, title index, name, class.
439  (see KEY_NODE_INFORMATION structure)
440 
441  KeyInformation -Supplies pointer to buffer to receive the data.
442 
443  Length - Length of KeyInformation in bytes.
444 
445  ResultLength - Number of bytes actually written into KeyInformation.
446 
447 Return Value:
448 
449  NTSTATUS
450 
451 --*/
452 {
453  NTSTATUS status;
454  HCELL_INDEX childcell;
455  PHHIVE Hive;
456  HCELL_INDEX Cell;
457  PCM_KEY_NODE Node;
458  HV_TRACK_CELL_REF CellRef = {0};
459 
460  CmKdPrintEx((DPFLTR_CONFIG_ID,CML_CM,"CmEnumerateKey\n"));
461 
462 
463  CmpLockRegistry();
464  //
465  // this should not be changed from under us
466  //
467  CmpLockKCBShared(KeyControlBlock);
468 
469  PERFINFO_REG_ENUM_KEY(KeyControlBlock, Index);
470 
471  if (KeyControlBlock->Delete) {
472  CmpUnlockKCB(KeyControlBlock);
473  CmpUnlockRegistry();
474  return STATUS_KEY_DELETED;
475  }
476 
477  Hive = KeyControlBlock->KeyHive;
478  Cell = KeyControlBlock->KeyCell;
479 
480  // Mark the hive as read only
481  CmpMarkAllBinsReadOnly(Hive);
482 
483  //
484  // fetch the child of interest
485  //
486 
487  Node = (PCM_KEY_NODE)HvGetCell(Hive, Cell);
488  if( Node == NULL ) {
489  //
490  // we couldn't map a view for the bin containing this cell
491  //
492  CmpUnlockKCB(KeyControlBlock);
493  CmpUnlockRegistry();
494  CmpMarkAllBinsReadOnly(Hive);
495  return STATUS_INSUFFICIENT_RESOURCES;
496 
497  }
498  childcell = CmpFindSubKeyByNumber(Hive, Node, Index);
499 
500  // release this cell here as we don't need this Node anymore
501  HvReleaseCell(Hive, Cell);
502 
503  if (childcell == HCELL_NIL) {
504  //
505  // no such child, clean up and return error
506  //
507  // we cannot return STATUS_INSUFFICIENT_RESOURCES because of Iop
508  // subsystem which treats INSUFFICIENT RESOURCES as no fatal error
509  //
510  CmpUnlockKCB(KeyControlBlock);
511  CmpUnlockRegistry();
512 
513  // Mark the hive as read only
514  CmpMarkAllBinsReadOnly(Hive);
515 
516  return STATUS_NO_MORE_ENTRIES;
517  }
518 
519  Node = (PCM_KEY_NODE)HvGetCell(Hive,childcell);
520  if( (Node == NULL) || !HvTrackCellRef(&CellRef,Hive,childcell) ) {
521  //
522  // we couldn't map a view for the bin containing this cell
523  //
524  CmpMarkAllBinsReadOnly(Hive);
525  CmpUnlockKCB(KeyControlBlock);
526  CmpUnlockRegistry();
527  return STATUS_INSUFFICIENT_RESOURCES;
528  }
529 
530  try {
531 
532  //
533  // call a worker to perform data transfer
534  //
535 
536  status = CmpQueryKeyData(Hive,
537  Node,
538  KeyInformationClass,
539  KeyInformation,
540  Length,
541  ResultLength
542  );
543 
544  } except (EXCEPTION_EXECUTE_HANDLER) {
545 
546  HvReleaseFreeCellRefArray(&CellRef);
547 
548  CmpUnlockKCB(KeyControlBlock);
549  CmpUnlockRegistry();
550  status = GetExceptionCode();
551 
552  // Mark the hive as read only
553  CmpMarkAllBinsReadOnly(Hive);
554 
555  return status;
556  }
557 
558  HvReleaseFreeCellRefArray(&CellRef);
559 
560  CmpUnlockKCB(KeyControlBlock);
561 
562  CmpUnlockRegistry();
563 
564  // Mark the hive as read only
565  CmpMarkAllBinsReadOnly(Hive);
566 
567  return status;
568 }
569

572 NTSTATUS
573 CmEnumerateValueKey(
574  IN PCM_KEY_CONTROL_BLOCK KeyControlBlock,
575  IN ULONG Index,
576  IN KEY_VALUE_INFORMATION_CLASS KeyValueInformationClass,
577  IN PVOID KeyValueInformation,
578  IN ULONG Length,
579  IN PULONG ResultLength
580  )
581 /*++
582 
583 Routine Description:
584 
585  The value entries of an open key may be enumerated.
586 
587  CmEnumerateValueKey returns the name of the Index'th value
588  entry of the open key specified by KeyHandle. The value
589  STATUS_NO_MORE_ENTRIES will be returned if value of Index is
590  larger than the number of sub keys.
591 
592  Note that Index is simply a way to select among value
593  entries. Two calls to NtEnumerateValueKey with the same Index
594  are NOT guaranteed to return the same results.
595 
596  If KeyValueInformation is not long enough to hold all requested data,
597  STATUS_BUFFER_OVERFLOW will be returned, and ResultLength will be
598  set to the number of bytes actually required.
599 
600 Arguments:
601 
602  KeyControlBlock - pointer to the KCB that describes the key
603 
604  Index - Specifies the (0-based) number of the sub key to be returned.
605 
606  KeyValueInformationClass - Specifies the type of information returned
607  in Buffer. One of the following types:
608 
609  KeyValueBasicInformation - return time of last write,
610  title index, and name. (See KEY_VALUE_BASIC_INFORMATION)
611 
612  KeyValueFullInformation - return time of last write,
613  title index, name, class. (See KEY_VALUE_FULL_INFORMATION)
614 
615  KeyValueInformation -Supplies pointer to buffer to receive the data.
616 
617  Length - Length of KeyValueInformation in bytes.
618 
619  ResultLength - Number of bytes actually written into KeyValueInformation.
620 
621 Return Value:
622 
623  NTSTATUS
624 
625 --*/
626 {
627  NTSTATUS status;
628  PHHIVE Hive;
629  PCM_KEY_NODE Node;
630  PCELL_DATA ChildList;
631  PCM_KEY_VALUE ValueData = NULL;
632  BOOLEAN IndexCached;
633  BOOLEAN ValueCached = FALSE;
634  PPCM_CACHED_VALUE ContainingList = NULL;
635  HCELL_INDEX ValueDataCellToRelease = HCELL_NIL;
636  HCELL_INDEX ValueListToRelease = HCELL_NIL;
637  VALUE_SEARCH_RETURN_TYPE SearchValue;
638 
639  CmKdPrintEx((DPFLTR_CONFIG_ID,CML_CM,"CmEnumerateValueKey\n"));
640 
641 
642  //
643  // lock the parent cell
644  //
645 
646  CmpLockRegistry();
647  //
648  // try shared first; we only upgrade to exclusive when there is a symlink or we need to populate the cache
649  //
650  CmpLockKCBShared(KeyControlBlock);
651 
652  PERFINFO_REG_ENUM_VALUE(KeyControlBlock, Index);
653 
654 RetryExclusive:
655  if (KeyControlBlock->Delete) {
656  CmpUnlockKCB(KeyControlBlock);
657  CmpUnlockRegistry();
658  return STATUS_KEY_DELETED;
659  }
660  Hive = KeyControlBlock->KeyHive;
661  Node = (PCM_KEY_NODE)HvGetCell(Hive, KeyControlBlock->KeyCell);
662  if( Node == NULL ) {
663  //
664  // we couldn't map a view for the bin containing this cell
665  //
666  CmpUnlockKCB(KeyControlBlock);
667  CmpUnlockRegistry();
668  return STATUS_INSUFFICIENT_RESOURCES;
669  }
670 
671  //
672  // fetch the child of interest
673  //
674  //
675  // Do it using the cache
676  //
677  if (Index >= KeyControlBlock->ValueCache.Count) {
678  //
679  // No such child, clean up and return error.
680  //
681  HvReleaseCell(Hive, KeyControlBlock->KeyCell);
682  CmpUnlockKCB(KeyControlBlock);
683  CmpUnlockRegistry();
684  return(STATUS_NO_MORE_ENTRIES);
685  }
686 
687  // Mark the hive as read only
688  CmpMarkAllBinsReadOnly(Hive);
689 
690  if (KeyControlBlock->ExtFlags & CM_KCB_SYM_LINK_FOUND) {
691  //
692  // The value list is now set to the KCB for symbolic link,
693  // Clean it up and set the value right before we do the query.
694  //
695  if( (CmpIsKCBLockedExclusive(KeyControlBlock) == FALSE) &&
696  (CmpTryConvertKCBLockSharedToExclusive(KeyControlBlock) == FALSE) ) {
697  //
698  // need to upgrade lock to exclusive
699  //
700  HvReleaseCell(Hive, KeyControlBlock->KeyCell);
701  CmpUpgradeKCBLockToExclusive(KeyControlBlock);
702  goto RetryExclusive;
703  }
704  CmpCleanUpKcbValueCache(KeyControlBlock);
705  CmpSetUpKcbValueCache(KeyControlBlock,Node->ValueList.Count,Node->ValueList.List);
706  }
707 
708  SearchValue = CmpGetValueListFromCache(KeyControlBlock,&ChildList, &IndexCached, &ValueListToRelease);
709  if( SearchValue == SearchNeedExclusiveLock ) {
710  //
711  // retry with exclusive lock, since we need to update the cache
712  //
713  ASSERT( ValueListToRelease == HCELL_NIL );
714  HvReleaseCell(Hive, KeyControlBlock->KeyCell);
715  CmpUpgradeKCBLockToExclusive(KeyControlBlock);
716  goto RetryExclusive;
717  }
718 
719  if (SearchValue != SearchSuccess) {
720  ASSERT( ChildList == NULL );
721 
722  if( ValueListToRelease != HCELL_NIL ) {
723  HvReleaseCell(Hive,ValueListToRelease);
724  }
725  HvReleaseCell(Hive, KeyControlBlock->KeyCell);
726  CmpUnlockKCB(KeyControlBlock);
727  CmpUnlockRegistry();
728  return(STATUS_INSUFFICIENT_RESOURCES);
729  }
730 
731  SearchValue = CmpGetValueKeyFromCache(KeyControlBlock, ChildList, Index, &ContainingList, &ValueData, IndexCached, &ValueCached,&ValueDataCellToRelease);
732  if( SearchValue == SearchNeedExclusiveLock ) {
733  //
734  // retry with exclusive lock, since we need to update the cache
735  //
736  ASSERT( ValueDataCellToRelease == HCELL_NIL );
737 
738  if( ValueListToRelease != HCELL_NIL ) {
739  HvReleaseCell(Hive,ValueListToRelease);
740  ValueListToRelease = HCELL_NIL;
741  }
742  HvReleaseCell(Hive, KeyControlBlock->KeyCell);
743 
744  CmpUpgradeKCBLockToExclusive(KeyControlBlock);
745  goto RetryExclusive;
746  }
747  if (SearchValue != SearchSuccess) {
748  ASSERT( ValueData == NULL );
749  status = STATUS_INSUFFICIENT_RESOURCES;
750  goto Exit;
751  }
752 
753  try {
754  //
755  // call a worker to perform data transfer; we are touching user-mode address; do it in a try/except
756  //
757  SearchValue = CmpQueryKeyValueData(KeyControlBlock,
758  ContainingList,
759  ValueData,
760  ValueCached,
761  KeyValueInformationClass,
762  KeyValueInformation,
763  Length,
764  ResultLength,
765  &status);
766  if( SearchValue == SearchNeedExclusiveLock ) {
767  //
768  // retry with exclusive lock, since we need to update the cache
769  //
770  if( ValueListToRelease != HCELL_NIL ) {
771  HvReleaseCell(Hive,ValueListToRelease);
772  }
773 
774  HvReleaseCell(Hive, KeyControlBlock->KeyCell);
775 
776  if( ValueDataCellToRelease != HCELL_NIL ) {
777  HvReleaseCell(Hive,ValueDataCellToRelease);
778  }
779  CmpUpgradeKCBLockToExclusive(KeyControlBlock);
780  goto RetryExclusive;
781  }
782  } except (EXCEPTION_EXECUTE_HANDLER) {
783  CmKdPrintEx((DPFLTR_CONFIG_ID,CML_EXCEPTION,"CmEnumerateValueKey: code:%08lx\n", GetExceptionCode()));
784  status = GetExceptionCode();
785  }
786 
787 Exit:
788  if( ValueListToRelease != HCELL_NIL ) {
789  HvReleaseCell(Hive,ValueListToRelease);
790  }
791  HvReleaseCell(Hive, KeyControlBlock->KeyCell);
792  if( ValueDataCellToRelease != HCELL_NIL ) {
793  HvReleaseCell(Hive,ValueDataCellToRelease);
794  }
795 
796  CmpUnlockKCB(KeyControlBlock);
797  CmpUnlockRegistry();
798  return status;
799 }
800 
801 NTSTATUS
802 CmFlushKey(
803  IN PCM_KEY_CONTROL_BLOCK Kcb,
804  IN BOOLEAN RegistryLockOwnedExclusive
805  )
806 /*++
807 
808 Routine Description:
809 
810  Forces changes made to a key to disk.
811 
812  CmFlushKey will not return to its caller until any changed data
813  associated with the key has been written out.
814 
815  WARNING: CmFlushKey will flush the entire registry tree, and thus will
816  burn cycles and I/O.
817 
818 Arguments:
819 
820  Hive - supplies a pointer to the hive control structure for the hive
821 
822  Cell - supplies index of node to whose sub keys are to be found
823 
824 Return Value:
825 
826  NTSTATUS
827 
828 --*/
829 {
830  PCMHIVE CmHive;
831  NTSTATUS status = STATUS_SUCCESS;
832  PHHIVE Hive;
833 
834  CmKdPrintEx((DPFLTR_CONFIG_ID,CML_CM,"CmFlushKey\n"));
835 
836 
837  //
838  // If writes are not working, lie and say we succeeded, will
839  // clean up in a short time. Only early system init code
840  // will ever know the difference.
841  //
842  if (CmpNoWrite) {
843  return STATUS_SUCCESS;
844  }
845 
846  Hive = Kcb->KeyHive;
847 
848  // Mark the hive as read only
849  CmpMarkAllBinsReadOnly(Hive);
850 
851  CmHive = CONTAINING_RECORD(Hive, CMHIVE, Hive);
852 
853  //
854  // Don't flush the master hive. If somebody asks for a flushkey on
855  // the master hive, do a CmpDoFlushAll instead. CmpDoFlushAll flushes
856  // every hive except the master hive, which is what they REALLY want.
857  //
858  if (CmHive == CmpMasterHive) {
859  CmpDoFlushAll(FALSE);
860  } else {
861  DCmCheckRegistry(CONTAINING_RECORD(Hive, CMHIVE, Hive));
862 
863  //
864  // no more writes to this hive while we are flushing it
865  //
866  CmpLockHiveFlusherExclusive(CmHive);
867  CmLockHiveViews (CmHive);
868 
869  if( HvHiveWillShrink( &(CmHive->Hive) ) ) {
870  //
871  // we may end up here is when the hive shrinks and we need
872  // exclusive access over the registry, as we are going to CcPurge !
873  //
874  CmUnlockHiveViews (CmHive);
875  if( !RegistryLockOwnedExclusive ) {
876  CmpUnlockHiveFlusher(CmHive);
877  ASSERT_KCB_LOCKED(Kcb);
878  CmpUnlockKCB(Kcb);
879  CmpUnlockRegistry();
880  CmpLockRegistryExclusive();
881  CmpLockHiveFlusherExclusive(CmHive);
882  CmpLockKCBShared(Kcb);
883  if(Kcb->Delete) {
884  CmpUnlockHiveFlusher(CmHive);
885  return STATUS_KEY_DELETED;
886  }
887 
888  if( CmHive->UseCount != 0) {
889  CmpFixHiveUsageCount(CmHive);
890  ASSERT( CmHive->UseCount == 0 );
891  }
892  }
893 #if DBG
894  else {
895  ASSERT_CM_LOCK_OWNED_EXCLUSIVE_OR_HIVE_LOADING(CmHive);
896  }
897 #endif
898  } else {
899  //
900  // release the views
901  //
902  CmUnlockHiveViews(CmHive);
903  }
904 
905  if (! HvSyncHive(Hive)) {
906 
907  status = STATUS_REGISTRY_IO_FAILED;
908 
909  CmKdPrintEx((DPFLTR_CONFIG_ID,CML_BUGCHECK,"CmFlushKey: HvSyncHive failed\n"));
910  }
911  CmpUnlockHiveFlusher(CmHive);
912  }
913 
914  // Mark the hive as read only
915  CmpMarkAllBinsReadOnly(Hive);
916 
917  return status;
918 }

921 NTSTATUS
922 CmQueryKey(
923  IN PCM_KEY_CONTROL_BLOCK KeyControlBlock,
924  IN KEY_INFORMATION_CLASS KeyInformationClass,
925  IN PVOID KeyInformation,
926  IN ULONG Length,
927  IN PULONG ResultLength
928  )
929 /*++
930 
931 Routine Description:
932 
933  Data about the class of a key, and the numbers and sizes of its
934  children and value entries may be queried with CmQueryKey.
935 
936  NOTE: The returned lengths are guaranteed to be at least as
937  long as the described values, but may be longer in
938  some circumstances.
939 
940 Arguments:
941 
942  KeyControlBlock - pointer to the KCB that describes the key
943 
944  KeyInformationClass - Specifies the type of information
945  returned in Buffer. One of the following types:
946 
947  KeyBasicInformation - return last write time, title index, and name.
948  (See KEY_BASIC_INFORMATION)
949 
950  KeyNodeInformation - return last write time, title index, name, class.
951  (See KEY_NODE_INFORMATION)
952 
953  KeyFullInformation - return all data except for name and security.
954  (See KEY_FULL_INFORMATION)
955 
956  KeyInformation -Supplies pointer to buffer to receive the data.
957 
958  Length - Length of KeyInformation in bytes.
959 
960  ResultLength - Number of bytes actually written into KeyInformation.
961 
962 Return Value:
963 
964  NTSTATUS
965 
966 --*/
967 {
968  NTSTATUS status = STATUS_UNSUCCESSFUL;
969  PCM_KEY_NODE Node = NULL;
970  PUNICODE_STRING Name = NULL;
971  HV_TRACK_CELL_REF CellRef = {0};
972 
973  CmKdPrintEx((DPFLTR_CONFIG_ID,CML_CM,"CmQueryKey\n"));
974 
975  CmpLockRegistry();
976  //
977  // should not be changing from under us
978  //
979  CmpLockKCBShared(KeyControlBlock);
980 
981  PERFINFO_REG_QUERY_KEY(KeyControlBlock);
982 
983  // Mark the hive as read only
984  CmpMarkAllBinsReadOnly(KeyControlBlock->KeyHive);
985 
986  try {
987 
988  //
989  // request for the FULL path of the key
990  //
991  if( KeyInformationClass == KeyNameInformation ) {
992  if (KeyControlBlock->Delete ) {
993  //
994  // special case: return key deleted status, but still fill the full name of the key.
995  //
996  status = STATUS_KEY_DELETED;
997  } else {
998  status = STATUS_SUCCESS;
999  }
1000 
1001  if( KeyControlBlock->NameBlock ) {
1002 
1003  Name = CmpConstructName(KeyControlBlock);
1004  if (Name == NULL) {
1005  status = STATUS_INSUFFICIENT_RESOURCES;
1006  } else {
1007  ULONG requiredlength;
1008  ULONG minimumlength;
1009  USHORT NameLength;
1010  LONG leftlength;
1011  PKEY_INFORMATION pbuffer = (PKEY_INFORMATION)KeyInformation;
1012 
1013  NameLength = Name->Length;
1014 
1015  requiredlength = FIELD_OFFSET(KEY_NAME_INFORMATION, Name) + NameLength;
1016 
1017  minimumlength = FIELD_OFFSET(KEY_NAME_INFORMATION, Name);
1018 
1019  *ResultLength = requiredlength;
1020  if (Length < minimumlength) {
1021 
1022  status = STATUS_BUFFER_TOO_SMALL;
1023 
1024  } else {
1025  //
1026  // Fill in the length of the name
1027  //
1028  pbuffer->KeyNameInformation.NameLength = NameLength;
1029 
1030  //
1031  // Now copy the full name into the user buffer, if enough space
1032  //
1033  leftlength = Length - minimumlength;
1034  requiredlength = NameLength;
1035  if (leftlength < (LONG)requiredlength) {
1036  requiredlength = leftlength;
1037  status = STATUS_BUFFER_OVERFLOW;
1038  }
1039 
1040  //
1041  // If not enough space, copy how much we can and return overflow
1042  //
1043  RtlCopyMemory(
1044  &(pbuffer->KeyNameInformation.Name[0]),
1045  Name->Buffer,
1046  requiredlength
1047  );
1048  }
1049  }
1050  }
1051  } else if(KeyControlBlock->Delete ) {
1052  //
1053  // key already deleted
1054  //
1055  status = STATUS_KEY_DELETED;
1056  } else if( KeyInformationClass == KeyFlagsInformation ) {
1057  //
1058  // we only want to get the user defined flags;
1059  //
1060  PKEY_INFORMATION pbuffer = (PKEY_INFORMATION)KeyInformation;
1061  ULONG requiredlength;
1062 
1063  requiredlength = sizeof(KEY_FLAGS_INFORMATION);
1064 
1065  *ResultLength = requiredlength;
1066 
1067  if (Length < requiredlength) {
1068  status = STATUS_BUFFER_TOO_SMALL;
1069  } else {
1070  pbuffer->KeyFlagsInformation.UserFlags = (ULONG)((USHORT)KeyControlBlock->Flags >> KEY_USER_FLAGS_SHIFT);
1071  status = STATUS_SUCCESS;
1072  }
1073  } else {
1074  //
1075  // call a worker to perform data transfer
1076  //
1077 
1078  if( KeyInformationClass == KeyCachedInformation ) {
1079  //
1080  // call the fast version
1081  //
1082  status = CmpQueryKeyDataFromCache( KeyControlBlock,
1083  KeyInformationClass,
1084  KeyInformation,
1085  Length,
1086  ResultLength);
1087  } else {
1088  //
1089  // old'n plain slow version
1090  //
1091  Node = (PCM_KEY_NODE)HvGetCell(KeyControlBlock->KeyHive, KeyControlBlock->KeyCell);
1092  if( (Node == NULL) || !HvTrackCellRef(&CellRef,KeyControlBlock->KeyHive, KeyControlBlock->KeyCell) ) {
1093  //
1094  // we couldn't map a view for the bin containing this cell
1095  //
1096  status = STATUS_INSUFFICIENT_RESOURCES;
1097  } else {
1098  status = CmpQueryKeyData(KeyControlBlock->KeyHive,
1099  Node,
1100  KeyInformationClass,
1101  KeyInformation,
1102  Length,
1103  ResultLength
1104  );
1105  }
1106  }
1107  }
1108 
1109  } finally {
1110  HvReleaseFreeCellRefArray(&CellRef);
1111 
1112  if( Name != NULL ) {
1113  ExFreePoolWithTag(Name, CM_NAME_TAG | PROTECTED_POOL);
1114  }
1115  CmpUnlockKCB(KeyControlBlock);
1116  CmpUnlockRegistry();
1117  }
1118 
1119  // Mark the hive as read only
1120  CmpMarkAllBinsReadOnly(KeyControlBlock->KeyHive);
1121 
1122  return status;
1123 }

1126 NTSTATUS
1127 CmQueryValueKey(
1128  IN PCM_KEY_CONTROL_BLOCK KeyControlBlock,
1129  IN UNICODE_STRING ValueName,
1130  IN KEY_VALUE_INFORMATION_CLASS KeyValueInformationClass,
1131  IN PVOID KeyValueInformation,
1132  IN ULONG Length,
1133  IN PULONG ResultLength
1134  )
1135 /*++
1136 
1137 Routine Description:
1138 
1139  The ValueName, TitleIndex, Type, and Data for any one of a key's
1140  value entries may be queried with CmQueryValueKey.
1141 
1142  If KeyValueInformation is not long enough to hold all requested data,
1143  STATUS_BUFFER_OVERFLOW will be returned, and ResultLength will be
1144  set to the number of bytes actually required.
1145 
1146 Arguments:
1147 
1148  KeyControlBlock - pointer to the KCB that describes the key
1149 
1150  ValueName - The name of the value entry to return data for.
1151 
1152  KeyValueInformationClass - Specifies the type of information
1153  returned in KeyValueInformation. One of the following types:
1154 
1155  KeyValueBasicInformation - return time of last write, title
1156  index, and name. (See KEY_VALUE_BASIC_INFORMATION)
1157 
1158  KeyValueFullInformation - return time of last write, title
1159  index, name, class. (See KEY_VALUE_FULL_INFORMATION)
1160 
1161  KeyValueInformation -Supplies pointer to buffer to receive the data.
1162 
1163  Length - Length of KeyValueInformation in bytes.
1164 
1165  ResultLength - Number of bytes actually written into KeyValueInformation.
1166 
1167 Return Value:
1168 
1169  NTSTATUS
1170 
1171 --*/
1172 {
1173  NTSTATUS status;
1174  PCM_KEY_VALUE ValueData = NULL;
1175  ULONG Index;
1176  BOOLEAN ValueCached = FALSE;
1177  PPCM_CACHED_VALUE ContainingList = NULL;
1178  HCELL_INDEX ValueDataCellToRelease = HCELL_NIL;
1179  VALUE_SEARCH_RETURN_TYPE SearchValue;
1180 
1181  CM_PAGED_CODE();
1182 
1183  CmKdPrintEx((DPFLTR_CONFIG_ID,CML_CM,"CmQueryValueKey\n"));
1184 
1185  CmpLockRegistry();
1186  //
1187  // try shared first, we'll only lock exclusive is symlink or cache not already set up
1188  //
1189  CmpLockKCBShared(KeyControlBlock);
1190  PERFINFO_REG_QUERY_VALUE(KeyControlBlock, &ValueName);
1191 
1192 RetryExclusive:
1193 
1194  if(KeyControlBlock->Delete) {
1195  CmpUnlockKCB(KeyControlBlock);
1196  CmpUnlockRegistry();
1197  return STATUS_KEY_DELETED;
1198  }
1199 
1200  if(KeyControlBlock->ExtFlags & CM_KCB_SYM_LINK_FOUND) {
1201  if( (CmpIsKCBLockedExclusive(KeyControlBlock) == FALSE) &&
1202  (CmpTryConvertKCBLockSharedToExclusive(KeyControlBlock) == FALSE) ) {
1203  //
1204  // need to upgrade lock to exclusive
1205  //
1206  CmpUpgradeKCBLockToExclusive(KeyControlBlock);
1207  goto RetryExclusive;
1208  }
1209  //
1210  // The value list is now set to the KCB for symbolic link,
1211  // Clean it up and set the value right before we do the query.
1212  //
1213  CmpCleanUpKcbValueCache(KeyControlBlock);
1214 
1215  {
1216  PCM_KEY_NODE Node = (PCM_KEY_NODE)HvGetCell(KeyControlBlock->KeyHive, KeyControlBlock->KeyCell);
1217  if( Node == NULL ) {
1218  //
1219  // we couldn't map a view for the bin containing this cell
1220  //
1221  status = STATUS_INSUFFICIENT_RESOURCES;
1222  goto ExitNoRelease;
1223  }
1224 
1225  CmpSetUpKcbValueCache(KeyControlBlock,Node->ValueList.Count,Node->ValueList.List);
1226 
1227  HvReleaseCell(KeyControlBlock->KeyHive, KeyControlBlock->KeyCell);
1228  }
1229  }
1230  //
1231  // Find the data
1232  //
1233 
1234  SearchValue = CmpFindValueByNameFromCache(KeyControlBlock,
1235  &ValueName,
1236  &ContainingList,
1237  &Index,
1238  &ValueData,
1239  &ValueCached,
1240  &ValueDataCellToRelease
1241  );
1242 
1243  if( SearchValue == SearchNeedExclusiveLock ) {
1244  //
1245  // retry with exclusive lock, since we need to update the cache
1246  //
1247  ASSERT( ValueDataCellToRelease == HCELL_NIL );
1248  ASSERT( ValueData == NULL );
1249  CmpUpgradeKCBLockToExclusive(KeyControlBlock);
1250  goto RetryExclusive;
1251  }
1252 
1253  if (SearchValue == SearchSuccess) {
1254  ASSERT( ValueData != NULL );
1255 
1256  try {
1257  //
1258  // call a worker to perform data transfer; we are touching user-mode address; do it in a try/except
1259  //
1260  SearchValue = CmpQueryKeyValueData(KeyControlBlock,
1261  ContainingList,
1262  ValueData,
1263  ValueCached,
1264  KeyValueInformationClass,
1265  KeyValueInformation,
1266  Length,
1267  ResultLength,
1268  &status);
1269  if( SearchValue == SearchNeedExclusiveLock ) {
1270  //
1271  // retry with exclusive lock, since we need to update the cache
1272  //
1273  if(ValueDataCellToRelease != HCELL_NIL) {
1274  HvReleaseCell(KeyControlBlock->KeyHive,ValueDataCellToRelease);
1275  ValueDataCellToRelease = HCELL_NIL;
1276  }
1277  CmpUpgradeKCBLockToExclusive(KeyControlBlock);
1278  goto RetryExclusive;
1279  }
1280 
1281  } except (EXCEPTION_EXECUTE_HANDLER) {
1282  CmKdPrintEx((DPFLTR_CONFIG_ID,CML_EXCEPTION,"CmQueryValueKey: code:%08lx\n", GetExceptionCode()));
1283  status = GetExceptionCode();
1284  }
1285  } else {
1286  status = STATUS_OBJECT_NAME_NOT_FOUND;
1287  }
1288 
1289 
1290  if(ValueDataCellToRelease != HCELL_NIL) {
1291  HvReleaseCell(KeyControlBlock->KeyHive,ValueDataCellToRelease);
1292  }
1293 
1294 ExitNoRelease:
1295  CmpUnlockKCB(KeyControlBlock);
1296  CmpUnlockRegistry();
1297 
1298  // Mark the hive as read only
1299  CmpMarkAllBinsReadOnly(KeyControlBlock->KeyHive);
1300 
1301  return status;
1302 }

1305 NTSTATUS
1306 CmQueryMultipleValueKey(
1307  IN PCM_KEY_CONTROL_BLOCK KeyControlBlock,
1308  IN PKEY_VALUE_ENTRY ValueEntries,
1309  IN ULONG EntryCount,
1310  IN PVOID ValueBuffer,
1311  IN OUT PULONG BufferLength,
1312  IN OPTIONAL PULONG ResultLength
1313  )
1314 /*++
1315 
1316 Routine Description:
1317 
1318  Multiple values of any key may be queried atomically with
1319  this api.
1320 
1321 Arguments:
1322 
1323  KeyControlBlock - Supplies the key to be queried.
1324 
1325  ValueEntries - Returns an array of KEY_VALUE_ENTRY structures, one for each value.
1326 
1327  EntryCount - Supplies the number of entries in the ValueNames and ValueEntries arrays
1328 
1329  ValueBuffer - Returns the value data for each value.
1330 
1331  BufferLength - Supplies the length of the ValueBuffer array in bytes.
1332  Returns the length of the ValueBuffer array that was filled in.
1333 
1334  ResultLength - if present, Returns the length in bytes of the ValueBuffer
1335  array required to return the requested values of this key.
1336 
1337 Return Value:
1338 
1339  NTSTATUS
1340 
1341 --*/
1342 
1343 {
1344  PHHIVE Hive;
1345  NTSTATUS Status;
1346  ULONG i;
1347  UNICODE_STRING CurrentName;
1348  HCELL_INDEX ValueCell = HCELL_NIL;
1349  PCM_KEY_VALUE ValueNode;
1350  ULONG RequiredLength = 0;
1351  ULONG UsedLength = 0;
1352  ULONG DataLength;
1353  BOOLEAN BufferFull = FALSE;
1354  BOOLEAN Small;
1355  KPROCESSOR_MODE PreviousMode;
1356  PCM_KEY_NODE Node;
1357 
1358  PAGED_CODE();
1359  CmKdPrintEx((DPFLTR_CONFIG_ID,CML_CM,"CmQueryMultipleValueKey\n"));
1360 
1361 
1362  CmpLockRegistry();
1363  CmpLockKCBShared(KeyControlBlock);
1364  if (KeyControlBlock->Delete) {
1365  CmpUnlockKCB(KeyControlBlock);
1366  CmpUnlockRegistry();
1367  return STATUS_KEY_DELETED;
1368  }
1369  Hive = KeyControlBlock->KeyHive;
1370  Status = STATUS_SUCCESS;
1371 
1372  Node = (PCM_KEY_NODE)HvGetCell(Hive, KeyControlBlock->KeyCell);
1373  if( Node == NULL ) {
1374  //
1375  // we couldn't map a view for the bin containing this cell
1376  //
1377  CmpUnlockKCB(KeyControlBlock);
1378  CmpUnlockRegistry();
1379  return STATUS_INSUFFICIENT_RESOURCES;
1380  }
1381 
1382  // Mark the hive as read only
1383  CmpMarkAllBinsReadOnly(Hive);
1384 
1385  PreviousMode = KeGetPreviousMode();
1386  try {
1387  for (i=0; i < EntryCount; i++) {
1388  //
1389  // find the data
1390  //
1391  if (PreviousMode == UserMode) {
1392  ProbeAndReadUnicodeStringEx(&CurrentName,ValueEntries[i].ValueName);
1393  ProbeForRead(CurrentName.Buffer,CurrentName.Length,sizeof(WCHAR));
1394  } else {
1395  CurrentName = *(ValueEntries[i].ValueName);
1396  }
1397 
1398  PERFINFO_REG_QUERY_MULTIVALUE(KeyControlBlock, &CurrentName);
1399 
1400  ValueCell = CmpFindValueByName(Hive,
1401  Node,
1402  &CurrentName);
1403  if (ValueCell != HCELL_NIL) {
1404 
1405  ValueNode = (PCM_KEY_VALUE)HvGetCell(Hive, ValueCell);
1406  if( ValueNode == NULL ) {
1407  //
1408  // we couldn't map a view for the bin containing this cell
1409  //
1410  ValueCell = HCELL_NIL;
1411  Status = STATUS_INSUFFICIENT_RESOURCES;
1412  break;
1413  }
1414  Small = CmpIsHKeyValueSmall(DataLength, ValueNode->DataLength);
1415 
1416  //
1417  // Round up UsedLength and RequiredLength to a ULONG boundary
1418  //
1419  UsedLength = (UsedLength + sizeof(ULONG)-1) & ~(sizeof(ULONG)-1);
1420  RequiredLength = (RequiredLength + sizeof(ULONG)-1) & ~(sizeof(ULONG)-1);
1421 
1422  //
1423  // If there is enough room for this data value in the buffer,
1424  // fill it in now. Otherwise, mark the buffer as full. We must
1425  // keep iterating through the values in order to determine the
1426  // RequiredLength.
1427  //
1428  if ((UsedLength + DataLength <= *BufferLength) &&
1429  (UsedLength + DataLength >= UsedLength) &&
1430  (!BufferFull)) {
1431  PCELL_DATA Buffer;
1432  BOOLEAN BufferAllocated;
1433  HCELL_INDEX CellToRelease;
1434  //
1435  // get the data from source, regardless of the size
1436  //
1437  if( CmpGetValueData(Hive,ValueNode,&DataLength,&Buffer,&BufferAllocated,&CellToRelease) == FALSE ) {
1438  //
1439  // insufficient resources; return NULL
1440  //
1441  ASSERT( BufferAllocated == FALSE );
1442  ASSERT( Buffer == NULL );
1443  Status = STATUS_INSUFFICIENT_RESOURCES;
1444  break;
1445  }
1446 
1447  RtlCopyMemory((PUCHAR)ValueBuffer + UsedLength,
1448  Buffer,
1449  DataLength);
1450  //
1451  // cleanup the temporary buffer
1452  //
1453  if( BufferAllocated == TRUE ) {
1454  ExFreePool( Buffer );
1455  }
1456  //
1457  // release the buffer in case we are using hive storage
1458  //
1459  if( CellToRelease != HCELL_NIL ) {
1460  HvReleaseCell(Hive,CellToRelease);
1461  }
1462 
1463  ValueEntries[i].Type = ValueNode->Type;
1464  ValueEntries[i].DataLength = DataLength;
1465  ValueEntries[i].DataOffset = UsedLength;
1466  UsedLength += DataLength;
1467  } else {
1468  BufferFull = TRUE;
1469  Status = STATUS_BUFFER_OVERFLOW;
1470  }
1471  RequiredLength += DataLength;
1472  HvReleaseCell(Hive, ValueCell);
1473  ValueCell = HCELL_NIL;
1474  } else {
1475  Status = STATUS_OBJECT_NAME_NOT_FOUND;
1476  break;
1477  }
1478  }
1479 
1480  if (NT_SUCCESS(Status) ||
1481  (Status == STATUS_BUFFER_OVERFLOW)) {
1482  *BufferLength = UsedLength;
1483  if (ARGUMENT_PRESENT(ResultLength)) {
1484  *ResultLength = RequiredLength;
1485  }
1486  }
1487 
1488  } finally {
1489  if( ValueCell != HCELL_NIL) {
1490  HvReleaseCell(Hive, ValueCell);
1491  }
1492  HvReleaseCell(Hive, KeyControlBlock->KeyCell);
1493 
1494  CmpUnlockKCB(KeyControlBlock);
1495  CmpUnlockRegistry();
1496  }
1497 
1498  // Mark the hive as read only
1499  CmpMarkAllBinsReadOnly(Hive);
1500 
1501  return Status;
1502 }

1504 NTSTATUS
1505 CmSetValueKey(
1506  IN PCM_KEY_CONTROL_BLOCK KeyControlBlock,
1507  IN PUNICODE_STRING ValueName,
1508  IN ULONG Type,
1509  IN PVOID Data,
1510  IN ULONG DataSize
1511  )
1512 /*++
1513 
1514 Routine Description:
1515 
1516  A value entry may be created or replaced with CmSetValueKey.
1517 
1518  If a value entry with a Value ID (i.e. name) matching the
1519  one specified by ValueName exists, it is deleted and replaced
1520  with the one specified. If no such value entry exists, a new
1521  one is created. NULL is a legal Value ID. While Value IDs must
1522  be unique within any given key, the same Value ID may appear
1523  in many different keys.
1524 
1525 Arguments:
1526 
1527  KeyControlBlock - pointer to kcb for the key to operate on
1528 
1529  ValueName - The unique (relative to the containing key) name
1530  of the value entry. May be NULL.
1531 
1532  Type - The integer type number of the value entry.
1533 
1534  Data - Pointer to buffer with actual data for the value entry.
1535 
1536  DataSize - Size of Data buffer.
1537 
1538 
1539 Return Value:
1540 
1541  NTSTATUS
1542 
1543 --*/
1544 {
1545  NTSTATUS status;
1546  PCM_KEY_NODE parent = NULL;
1547  HCELL_INDEX oldchild = 0;
1548  ULONG count;
1549  PHHIVE Hive = NULL;
1550  HCELL_INDEX Cell;
1551  ULONG StorageType;
1552  ULONG TempData;
1553  BOOLEAN found;
1554  PCM_KEY_VALUE Value = NULL;
1555  LARGE_INTEGER systemtime;
1556  ULONG mustChange=FALSE;
1557  ULONG ChildIndex;
1558  HCELL_INDEX ParentToRelease = HCELL_NIL;
1559  HCELL_INDEX ChildToRelease = HCELL_NIL;
1560  BOOLEAN FlusherLocked = FALSE;
1561  VALUE_SEARCH_RETURN_TYPE SearchType;
1562 
1563  PERFINFO_REG_SET_VALUE_DECL();
1564 
1565  CmKdPrintEx((DPFLTR_CONFIG_ID,CML_CM,"CmSetValueKey\n"));
1566 
1567  CmpLockRegistry();
1568  //
1569  // try shared first; we'll only lock exclusive if we're going to change the cache
1570  //
1571  CmpLockKCBShared(KeyControlBlock);
1572 
1573  ASSERT(sizeof(ULONG) == CM_KEY_VALUE_SMALL);
1574 
1575  PERFINFO_REG_SET_VALUE(KeyControlBlock);
1576 
1577  // Mark the hive as read only
1578  CmpMarkAllBinsReadOnly(KeyControlBlock->KeyHive);
1579 
1580  while (TRUE) {
1581 TryAgain:
1582  //
1583  // Check that we are not being asked to add a value to a key
1584  // that has been deleted
1585  //
1586  if (KeyControlBlock->Delete == TRUE) {
1587  status = STATUS_KEY_DELETED;
1588  goto Exit;
1589  }
1590 
1591  ASSERT_KCB_LOCKED(KeyControlBlock);
1592  //
1593  // Check to see if this is a symbolic link node. If so caller
1594  // is only allowed to create/change the SymbolicLinkValue
1595  // value name
1596  //
1597 
1598  if (KeyControlBlock->Flags & KEY_SYM_LINK &&
1599  (( (Type != REG_LINK) ) ||
1600  ValueName == NULL ||
1601  !RtlEqualUnicodeString(&CmSymbolicLinkValueName, ValueName, TRUE)))
1602  {
1603  //
1604  // Disallow attempts to manipulate any value names under a symbolic link
1605  // except for the "SymbolicLinkValue" value name or type other than REG_LINK
1606  //
1607 
1608  // Mark the hive as read only
1609  CmpMarkAllBinsReadOnly(KeyControlBlock->KeyHive);
1610 
1611  status = STATUS_ACCESS_DENIED;
1612  goto Exit;
1613  }
1614 
1615  if( mustChange == FALSE ) {
1616  //
1617  // first iteration; look inside the kcb cache
1618  //
1619 
1620  SearchType = CmpCompareNewValueDataAgainstKCBCache(KeyControlBlock,ValueName,Type,Data,DataSize);
1621  if( SearchType == SearchNeedExclusiveLock ) {
1622  CmpUpgradeKCBLockToExclusive(KeyControlBlock);
1623  goto TryAgain;
1624  } else if( SearchType == SearchSuccess) {
1625  //
1626  // the value is in the cache and is the same; make this call a noop
1627  //
1628  status = STATUS_SUCCESS;
1629  goto Exit;
1630  }
1631 
1632  //
1633  // To Get here, we must either be changing a value, or setting a new one
1634  // we need to upgrade kcb lock if not yet exclusive
1635  //
1636  if( (CmpIsKCBLockedExclusive(KeyControlBlock) == FALSE) &&
1637  (CmpTryConvertKCBLockSharedToExclusive(KeyControlBlock) == FALSE) ) {
1638  //
1639  // need to upgrade lock to exclusive
1640  //
1641  CmpUpgradeKCBLockToExclusive(KeyControlBlock);
1642  }
1643  mustChange=TRUE;
1644  } else {
1645  //
1646  // second iteration; look inside the hive
1647  //
1648 
1649 
1650  //
1651  // get reference to parent key,
1652  //
1653  Hive = KeyControlBlock->KeyHive;
1654  Cell = KeyControlBlock->KeyCell;
1655  if( ParentToRelease != HCELL_NIL ) {
1656  HvReleaseCell(Hive,ParentToRelease);
1657  ParentToRelease = HCELL_NIL;
1658  }
1659  parent = (PCM_KEY_NODE)HvGetCell(Hive, Cell);
1660  if( parent == NULL ) {
1661  //
1662  // we couldn't map a view for the bin containing this cell
1663  //
1664 
1665  status = STATUS_INSUFFICIENT_RESOURCES;
1666  goto Exit;
1667  }
1668  ParentToRelease = Cell;
1669  //
1670  // try to find an existing value entry by the same name
1671  //
1672  count = parent->ValueList.Count;
1673  found = FALSE;
1674 
1675  if (count > 0) {
1676  if( CmpFindNameInList(Hive,
1677  &parent->ValueList,
1678  ValueName,
1679  &ChildIndex,
1680  &oldchild) == FALSE ) {
1681  //
1682  // we couldn't map a view for the bin containing this cell
1683  //
1684 
1685  status = STATUS_INSUFFICIENT_RESOURCES;
1686  goto Exit;
1687  }
1688 
1689  if (oldchild != HCELL_NIL) {
1690  if( ChildToRelease != HCELL_NIL ) {
1691  HvReleaseCell(Hive,ChildToRelease);
1692  ChildToRelease = HCELL_NIL;
1693  }
1694  Value = (PCM_KEY_VALUE)HvGetCell(Hive,oldchild);
1695  if( Value == NULL ) {
1696  //
1697  // could no map view
1698  //
1699  status = STATUS_INSUFFICIENT_RESOURCES;
1700  goto Exit;
1701  }
1702  ChildToRelease = oldchild;
1703  found = TRUE;
1704  }
1705  } else {
1706  //
1707  // empty list; add it first
1708  //
1709  ChildIndex = 0;
1710  }
1711 
1712  //
1713  // Performance Hack:
1714  // If a Set is asking us to set a key to the current value (IE does this a lot)
1715  // drop it (and, therefore, the last modified time) on the floor, but return success
1716  // this stops the page from being dirtied, and us having to flush the registry.
1717  //
1718  //
1719  break;
1720  }
1721 
1722  //
1723  // We're going through these gyrations so that if someone does come in and try and delete the
1724  // key we're setting we're safe. Once we know we have to change the key, take the
1725  // flusher lock and restart
1726  //
1727  //
1728  ASSERT( !FlusherLocked );
1729  CmpLockHiveFlusherShared((PCMHIVE)KeyControlBlock->KeyHive);
1730  FlusherLocked = TRUE;
1731 
1732  }// while
1733 
1734  ASSERT( mustChange == TRUE );
1735 
1736  ASSERT_KCB_LOCKED_EXCLUSIVE(KeyControlBlock);
1737 
1738  // It's a different or new value, mark it dirty, since we'll
1739  // at least set its time stamp
1740 
1741  if (! HvMarkCellDirty(Hive, Cell, FALSE)) {
1742  status = STATUS_NO_LOG_SPACE;
1743  goto Exit;
1744  }
1745 
1746  StorageType = HvGetCellType(Cell);
1747 
1748  //
1749  // stash small data if relevant
1750  //
1751  TempData = 0;
1752  if ((DataSize <= CM_KEY_VALUE_SMALL) &&
1753  (DataSize > 0))
1754  {
1755  try {
1756  RtlCopyMemory( // yes, move memory, could be 1 byte
1757  &TempData, // at the end of a page.
1758  Data,
1759  DataSize
1760  );
1761  } except (EXCEPTION_EXECUTE_HANDLER) {
1762  CmKdPrintEx((DPFLTR_CONFIG_ID,CML_EXCEPTION,"!!CmSetValueKey: code:%08lx\n", GetExceptionCode()));
1763  status = GetExceptionCode();
1764  goto Exit;
1765  }
1766  }
1767 
1768  if (found) {
1769 
1770  //
1771  // ----- Existing Value Entry Path -----
1772  //
1773 
1774  //
1775  // An existing value entry of the specified name exists,
1776  // set our data into it.
1777  //
1778  status = CmpSetValueKeyExisting(Hive,
1779  oldchild,
1780  Value,
1781  Type,
1782  Data,
1783  DataSize,
1784  StorageType,
1785  TempData);
1786 
1787  PERFINFO_REG_SET_VALUE_EXIST();
1788  } else {
1789 
1790  //
1791  // ----- New Value Entry Path -----
1792  //
1793 
1794  //
1795  // Either there are no existing value entries, or the one
1796  // specified is not in the list. In either case, create and
1797  // fill a new one, and add it to the list
1798  //
1799  status = CmpSetValueKeyNew(Hive,
1800  parent,
1801  ValueName,
1802  ChildIndex,
1803  Type,
1804  Data,
1805  DataSize,
1806  StorageType,
1807  TempData);
1808  PERFINFO_REG_SET_VALUE_NEW();
1809  }
1810 
1811  if (NT_SUCCESS(status)) {
1812 
1813  // sanity assert
1814  ASSERT( parent->MaxValueNameLen == KeyControlBlock->KcbMaxValueNameLen );
1815  if (parent->MaxValueNameLen < ValueName->Length) {
1816  parent->MaxValueNameLen = ValueName->Length;
1817  // update the kcb cache too
1818  KeyControlBlock->KcbMaxValueNameLen = ValueName->Length;
1819  }
1820 
1821  //sanity assert
1822  ASSERT( parent->MaxValueDataLen == KeyControlBlock->KcbMaxValueDataLen );
1823  if (parent->MaxValueDataLen < DataSize) {
1824  parent->MaxValueDataLen = DataSize;
1825  // update the kcb cache too
1826  KeyControlBlock->KcbMaxValueDataLen = parent->MaxValueDataLen;
1827  }
1828 
1829  KeQuerySystemTime(&systemtime);
1830  parent->LastWriteTime = systemtime;
1831  // update the kcb cache too.
1832  KeyControlBlock->KcbLastWriteTime = systemtime;
1833 
1834  if( found && (CMP_IS_CELL_CACHED(KeyControlBlock->ValueCache.ValueList)) ) {
1835  //
1836  // invalidate only the entry we changed.
1837  //
1838  PULONG_PTR CachedList = (PULONG_PTR) CMP_GET_CACHED_CELLDATA(KeyControlBlock->ValueCache.ValueList);
1839  if (CMP_IS_CELL_CACHED(CachedList[ChildIndex])) {
1840 
1841  ExFreePool((PVOID) CMP_GET_CACHED_ADDRESS(CachedList[ChildIndex]));
1842  }
1843  CachedList[ChildIndex] = oldchild;
1844 
1845  } else {
1846  //
1847  // rebuild ALL KCB cache
1848  //
1849  CmpCleanUpKcbValueCache(KeyControlBlock);
1850  CmpSetUpKcbValueCache(KeyControlBlock,parent->ValueList.Count,parent->ValueList.List);
1851  }
1852  CmpReportNotify(KeyControlBlock,
1853  KeyControlBlock->KeyHive,
1854  KeyControlBlock->KeyCell,
1855  REG_NOTIFY_CHANGE_LAST_SET);
1856  }
1857 
1858 Exit:
1859  PERFINFO_REG_SET_VALUE_DONE(ValueName);
1860 
1861  if( ParentToRelease != HCELL_NIL && Hive != NULL) {
1862  HvReleaseCell(Hive,ParentToRelease);
1863  }
1864  if( ChildToRelease != HCELL_NIL && Hive != NULL) {
1865  HvReleaseCell(Hive,ChildToRelease);
1866  }
1867 
1868  if( FlusherLocked ) {
1869  CmpUnlockHiveFlusher((PCMHIVE)KeyControlBlock->KeyHive);
1870  }
1871 
1872  CmpUnlockKCB(KeyControlBlock);
1873  CmpUnlockRegistry();
1874 
1875  // Mark the hive as read only
1876  CmpMarkAllBinsReadOnly(KeyControlBlock->KeyHive);
1877 
1878  return status;
1879 }

1882 NTSTATUS
1883 CmpSetValueKeyExisting(
1884  IN PHHIVE Hive,
1885  IN HCELL_INDEX OldChild,
1886  IN PCM_KEY_VALUE Value,
1887  IN ULONG Type,
1888  IN PVOID Data,
1889  IN ULONG DataSize,
1890  IN ULONG StorageType,
1891  IN ULONG TempData
1892  )
1893 /*++
1894 
1895 Routine Description:
1896 
1897  Helper for CmSetValueKey, implements the case where the value entry
1898  being set already exists.
1899 
1900 Arguments:
1901 
1902  Hive - hive of interest
1903 
1904  OldChild - hcell_index of the value entry body to which we are to
1905  set new data
1906 
1907  Type - The integer type number of the value entry.
1908 
1909  Data - Pointer to buffer with actual data for the value entry.
1910 
1911  DataSize - Size of Data buffer.
1912 
1913  StorageType - stable or volatile
1914 
1915  TempData - small values are passed here
1916 
1917 Return Value:
1918 
1919  STATUS_SUCCESS if it worked, appropriate status code if it did not
1920 
1921 Note:
1922 
1923  For new hives format, we have the following cases:
1924 
1925  New Data Old Data
1926  -------- --------
1927 
1928 1. small small
1929 2. small normal
1930 3. small bigdata
1931 4. normal small
1932 5. normal normal
1933 6. normal bigdata
1934 7. bigdata small
1935 8. bigdata normal
1936 9. bigdata bigdata
1937 
1938 
1939 
1940 --*/
1941 {
1942  HCELL_INDEX DataCell;
1943  HCELL_INDEX OldDataCell;
1944  PCELL_DATA pdata;
1945  HCELL_INDEX NewCell;
1946  ULONG OldRealSize;
1947  USHORT OldSizeType; // 0 - small
1948  USHORT NewSizeType; // 1 - normal
1949  // 2 - bigdata
1950  HANDLE hSecure = 0;
1951  NTSTATUS status = STATUS_SUCCESS;
1952 
1953  ASSERT_HIVE_FLUSHER_LOCKED((PCMHIVE)Hive);
1954 
1955  //
1956  // value entry by the specified name already exists
1957  // oldchild is hcell_index of its value entry body
1958  // which we will always edit, so mark it dirty
1959  //
1960  if (! HvMarkCellDirty(Hive, OldChild, FALSE)) {
1961  return STATUS_NO_LOG_SPACE;
1962  }
1963 
1964  if(CmpIsHKeyValueSmall(OldRealSize, Value->DataLength) == TRUE ) {
1965  //
1966  // old data was small
1967  //
1968  OldSizeType = 0;
1969  } else if( CmpIsHKeyValueBig(Hive,OldRealSize) == TRUE ) {
1970  //
1971  // old data was big
1972  //
1973  OldSizeType = 2;
1974  } else {
1975  //
1976  // old data was normal
1977  //
1978  OldSizeType = 1;
1979  }
1980 
1981  if( DataSize <= CM_KEY_VALUE_SMALL ) {
1982  //
1983  // new data is small
1984  //
1985  NewSizeType = 0;
1986  } else if( CmpIsHKeyValueBig(Hive,DataSize) == TRUE ) {
1987  //
1988  // new data is big
1989  //
1990  NewSizeType = 2;
1991  } else {
1992  //
1993  // new data is normal
1994  //
1995  NewSizeType = 1;
1996  }
1997 
1998 
1999  //
2000  // this will handle all cases and will make sure data is marked dirty
2001  //
2002  if( !CmpMarkValueDataDirty(Hive,Value) ) {
2003  return STATUS_NO_LOG_SPACE;
2004  }
2005 
2006  //
2007  // cases 1,2,3
2008  //
2009  if( NewSizeType == 0 ) {
2010  if( ((OldSizeType == 1) && (OldRealSize > 0) ) ||
2011  (OldSizeType == 2)
2012  ) {
2013  CmpFreeValueData(Hive,Value->Data,OldRealSize);
2014  }
2015 
2016  //
2017  // write our new small data into value entry body
2018  //
2019  Value->DataLength = DataSize + CM_KEY_VALUE_SPECIAL_SIZE;
2020  Value->Data = TempData;
2021  Value->Type = Type;
2022 
2023  return STATUS_SUCCESS;
2024  }
2025 
2026  //
2027  // secure the user buffer so we don't get inconsistencies.
2028  // ONLY if we are called with a user mode buffer !!!
2029  //
2030 
2031  if ( (ULONG_PTR)Data <= (ULONG_PTR)MM_HIGHEST_USER_ADDRESS ) {
2032  hSecure = MmSecureVirtualMemory(Data,DataSize, PAGE_READONLY);
2033  if (hSecure == 0) {
2034  return STATUS_INVALID_PARAMETER;
2035  }
2036  }
2037 
2038  //
2039  // store it to be freed if the allocation succeeds
2040  //
2041  OldDataCell = Value->Data;
2042 
2043  //
2044  // cases 4,5,6
2045  //
2046  if( NewSizeType == 1 ){
2047 
2048  if( (OldSizeType == 1) && (OldRealSize > 0)) {
2049  //
2050  // we already have a cell; see if we can reuse it !
2051  //
2052  DataCell = Value->Data;
2053  ASSERT(DataCell != HCELL_NIL);
2054  pdata = HvGetCell(Hive, DataCell);
2055  if( pdata == NULL ) {
2056  //
2057  // we couldn't map a view for the bin containing this cell
2058  //
2059  status = STATUS_INSUFFICIENT_RESOURCES;
2060  goto Exit;
2061  }
2062  // release it right here, as the registry is locked exclusively, so we don't care
2063  HvReleaseCell(Hive, DataCell);
2064 
2065  ASSERT(HvGetCellSize(Hive, pdata) > 0);
2066 
2067  if (DataSize <= (ULONG)(HvGetCellSize(Hive, pdata))) {
2068 
2069  //
2070  // The existing data cell is big enough to hold the new data.
2071  //
2072 
2073  //
2074  // we'll keep this cell
2075  //
2076  NewCell = DataCell;
2077 
2078  } else {
2079  //
2080  // grow the existing cell
2081  //
2082  NewCell = HvReallocateCell(Hive,DataCell,DataSize);
2083  if (NewCell == HCELL_NIL) {
2084  status = STATUS_INSUFFICIENT_RESOURCES;
2085  goto Exit;
2086  }
2087  }
2088 
2089  } else {
2090  //
2091  // allocate a new cell
2092  //
2093  NewCell = HvAllocateCell(Hive, DataSize, StorageType,(HvGetCellType(OldChild)==StorageType)?OldChild:HCELL_NIL);
2094 
2095  if (NewCell == HCELL_NIL) {
2096  status = STATUS_INSUFFICIENT_RESOURCES;
2097  goto Exit;
2098  }
2099  }
2100 
2101  //
2102  // now we have a cell that can accommodate the data
2103  //
2104  pdata = HvGetCell(Hive, NewCell);
2105  if( pdata == NULL ) {
2106  //
2107  // we couldn't map a view for the bin containing this cell
2108  //
2109  // this shouldn't happen as we just allocated/ reallocated/ marked dirty this cell
2110  //
2111  ASSERT( FALSE );
2112  status = STATUS_INSUFFICIENT_RESOURCES;
2113  goto Exit;
2114  }
2115  // release it right here, as the registry is locked exclusively, so we don't care
2116  HvReleaseCell(Hive, NewCell);
2117 
2118  //
2119  // copy the actual data
2120  //
2121  RtlCopyMemory(pdata,Data,DataSize);
2122  Value->Data = NewCell;
2123  Value->DataLength = DataSize;
2124  Value->Type = Type;
2125 
2126  // sanity
2127  ASSERT_CELL_DIRTY(Hive,NewCell);
2128 
2129  if( OldSizeType == 2 ) {
2130  //
2131  // old data was big; free it
2132  //
2133  ASSERT( OldDataCell != NewCell );
2134  CmpFreeValueData(Hive,OldDataCell,OldRealSize);
2135  }
2136 
2137  status = STATUS_SUCCESS;
2138  goto Exit;
2139  }
2140 
2141  //
2142  // cases 7,8,9
2143  //
2144  if( NewSizeType == 2 ) {
2145 
2146  if( OldSizeType == 2 ) {
2147  //
2148  // data was previously big; grow it!
2149  //
2150 
2151  status =CmpSetValueDataExisting(Hive,Data,DataSize,StorageType,OldDataCell);
2152  if( !NT_SUCCESS(status) ) {
2153  goto Exit;
2154  }
2155  NewCell = OldDataCell;
2156 
2157  } else {
2158  //
2159  // data was small or normal.
2160  // allocate and copy to a new big data cell;
2161  // then free the old cell
2162  //
2163  status = CmpSetValueDataNew(Hive,Data,DataSize,StorageType,OldChild,&NewCell);
2164  if( !NT_SUCCESS(status) ) {
2165  //
2166  // We have bombed out loading user data, clean up and exit.
2167  //
2168  goto Exit;
2169  }
2170 
2171  if( (OldSizeType != 0) && (OldRealSize != 0) ) {
2172  //
2173  // there is something to free
2174  //
2175  HvFreeCell(Hive, Value->Data);
2176  }
2177  }
2178 
2179  Value->DataLength = DataSize;
2180  Value->Data = NewCell;
2181  Value->Type = Type;
2182 
2183  // sanity
2184  ASSERT_CELL_DIRTY(Hive,NewCell);
2185 
2186  status = STATUS_SUCCESS;
2187  goto Exit;
2188 
2189  }
2190 
2191  //
2192  // we shouldn't get here
2193  //
2194  ASSERT( FALSE );
2195 
2196 Exit:
2197  if( hSecure) {
2198  MmUnsecureVirtualMemory(hSecure);
2199  }
2200  return status;
2201 }

2203 NTSTATUS
2204 CmpSetValueKeyNew(
2205  IN PHHIVE Hive,

2212  IN ULONG StorageType,
2213  IN ULONG TempData

2215 /*++
2216 
2217 Routine Description:
2218 
2219  Helper for CmSetValueKey, implements the case where the value entry
2220  being set does not exist. Will create new value entry and data,
2221  place in list (which may be created)
2222 
2223 Arguments:
2224 
2225  Hive - hive of interest
2226 
2227  Parent - pointer to key node value entry is for
2228 
2229  ValueName - The unique (relative to the containing key) name
2230  of the value entry. May be NULL.
2231 
2232  Index - where in the list should this value be inserted
2233 
2234  Type - The integer type number of the value entry.
2235 
2236  Data - Pointer to buffer with actual data for the value entry.
2237 
2238  DataSize - Size of Data buffer.
2239 
2240  StorageType - stable or volatile
2241 
2242  TempData - small data values passed here
2243 
2244 
2245 Return Value:
2246 
2247  STATUS_SUCCESS if it worked, appropriate status code if it did not
2248 
2249 --*/
2250 {
2251  PCELL_DATA pvalue;
2252  HCELL_INDEX ValueCell;
2253  NTSTATUS Status;
2254 
2255  ASSERT_HIVE_FLUSHER_LOCKED((PCMHIVE)Hive);
2256 
2257  //
2258  // Either Count == 0 (no list) or our entry is simply not in
2259  // the list. Create a new value entry body, and data. Add to list.
2260  // (May create the list.)
2261  //
2262  if (Parent->ValueList.Count != 0) {
2263  ASSERT(Parent->ValueList.List != HCELL_NIL);
2264  if (! HvMarkCellDirty(Hive, Parent->ValueList.List, FALSE)) {
2265  return STATUS_NO_LOG_SPACE;
2266  }
2267  }
2268 
2269  //
2270  // allocate the body of the value entry, and the data
2271  //
2272  ValueCell = HvAllocateCell(
2273  Hive,
2274  CmpHKeyValueSize(Hive, ValueName),
2275  StorageType,

2453  IN PCM_KEY_CONTROL_BLOCK KeyControlBlock,
2454  IN ULONG UserFlags
2455  )

2457 
2458 Routine Description:
2459 
2460  Sets the user defined flags for the key; At this point there are only
2461  4 bits reserved for user defined flags. kcb and knode must be kept in
2462  sync.

2464 Arguments:
2465

2467 
2468  UserFlags - user defined flags to be set on this key.
2469 
2470 Return Value:
2471 
2472  NTSTATUS
2473 
2474 --*/
2475 {
2476  PCM_KEY_NODE Node;
2477  PHHIVE Hive;
2478  HCELL_INDEX Cell;
2479  LARGE_INTEGER LastWriteTime;
2480  NTSTATUS status = STATUS_SUCCESS;
2481 
2482  CmKdPrintEx((DPFLTR_CONFIG_ID,CML_CM,"CmSetKeyUserFlags\n"));
2483 
2484  CmpLockRegistry();
2485  //
2486  // serialize access to this key.
2487  //
2488  CmpLockKCBExclusive(KeyControlBlock);
2489 
2490  //
2491  // Check that we are not being asked to modify a key
2492  // that has been deleted
2493  //
2494  if (KeyControlBlock->Delete == TRUE) {
2495  status = STATUS_KEY_DELETED;
2496  goto Exit;
2497  }
2498 
2499  if( UserFlags & (~((ULONG)KEY_USER_FLAGS_VALID_MASK)) ) {
2500  //
2501  // number of user defined flags exceeded; punt
2502  //
2503  status = STATUS_INVALID_PARAMETER;
2504  goto Exit;
2505 
2506  }
2507 
2508  Hive = KeyControlBlock->KeyHive;
2509  Cell = KeyControlBlock->KeyCell;
2510

2512  // no flush from this point on
2513  //

2517  status = STATUS_NO_LOG_SPACE;

2519  }

2525  //
2526

2546  KeyControlBlock->KcbLastWriteTime = LastWriteTime;

2550  CmpUnlockHiveFlusher((PCMHIVE)Hive);

2644 NTSTATUS
2645 CmLoadKey(
2646  IN POBJECT_ATTRIBUTES TargetKey,
2647  IN POBJECT_ATTRIBUTES SourceFile,
2648  IN ULONG Flags,
2649  IN PCM_KEY_BODY KeyBody
2650  )
2651 
2652 /*++
2653 
2654 Routine Description:
2655 
2656  A hive (file in the format created by NtSaveKey) may be linked
2657  into the active registry with this call. UNLIKE NtRestoreKey,
2658  the file specified to NtLoadKey will become the actual backing
2659  store of part of the registry (that is, it will NOT be copied.)
2660 
2661  The file may have an associated .log file.
2662 
2663  If the hive file is marked as needing a .log file, and one is
2664  not present, the call will fail.
2665 
2666  The name specified by SourceFile must be such that ".log" can
2667  be appended to it to generate the name of the log file. Thus,
2668  on FAT file systems, the hive file may not have an extension.
2669 
2670  This call is used by logon to make the user's profile available
2671  in the registry. It is not intended for use doing backup,
2672  restore, etc. Use NtRestoreKey for that.
2673 
2674  N.B. This routine assumes that the object attributes for the file
2675  to be opened have been captured into kernel space so that
2676  they can safely be passed to the worker thread to open the file
2677  and do the actual I/O.
2678 
2679 Arguments:
2680 
2681  TargetKey - specifies the path to a key to link the hive to.
2682  path must be of the form "\registry\user<username>"
2683 
2684  SourceFile - specifies a file. while file could be remote,
2685  that is strongly discouraged.
2686 
2687  Flags - specifies any flags that should be used for the load operation.
2688  The only valid flag is REG_NO_LAZY_FLUSH.
2689 
2690 Return Value:
2691 
2692  NTSTATUS
2693 
2694 --*/
2695 {
2696  PCMHIVE NewHive = NULL;
2697  NTSTATUS Status;
2698  BOOLEAN Allocate;
2699  SECURITY_QUALITY_OF_SERVICE ServiceQos;
2700  SECURITY_CLIENT_CONTEXT ClientSecurityContext;
2701  HANDLE KeyHandle;
2702  PCMHIVE OtherHive = NULL;
2703  CM_PARSE_CONTEXT ParseContext;
2704 
2705 
2706  if( KeyBody != NULL ) {
2707  OtherHive = (PCMHIVE)CONTAINING_RECORD(KeyBody->KeyControlBlock->KeyHive, CMHIVE, Hive);
2708  if( ! (OtherHive->Flags & CM_CMHIVE_FLAG_UNTRUSTED) ) {
2709  //
2710  // deny attempts to join the TRUSTED class of trust
2711  //
2712  return STATUS_INVALID_PARAMETER;
2713  }
2714  }
2715 
2716 
2717  //
2718  // Obtain the security context here so we can use it
2719  // later to impersonate the user, which we will do
2720  // if we cannot access the file as SYSTEM. This
2721  // usually occurs if the file is on a remote machine.
2722  //
2723  ServiceQos.Length = sizeof(SECURITY_QUALITY_OF_SERVICE);
2724  ServiceQos.ImpersonationLevel = SecurityImpersonation;
2725  ServiceQos.ContextTrackingMode = SECURITY_DYNAMIC_TRACKING;
2726  ServiceQos.EffectiveOnly = TRUE;
2727  Status = SeCreateClientSecurity(CONTAINING_RECORD(KeGetCurrentThread(),ETHREAD,Tcb),
2728  &ServiceQos,
2729  FALSE,
2730  &ClientSecurityContext);
2731  if (!NT_SUCCESS(Status)) {
2732  return(Status);
2733  }
2734 
2735  RtlZeroMemory(&ParseContext,sizeof(CM_PARSE_CONTEXT));
2736  ParseContext.CreateOperation = FALSE;
2737  //
2738  // we open the root of the hive here. if it already exists,this will prevent it from going
2739  // away from under us while we are doing the "already loaded" check (due to delay unload logic)
2740  //
2741  Status = ObOpenObjectByName(TargetKey,
2742  CmpKeyObjectType,
2743  KernelMode,
2744  NULL,
2745  KEY_READ,
2746  (PVOID)&ParseContext,
2747  &KeyHandle);
2748  if(!NT_SUCCESS(Status)) {
2749  KeyHandle = NULL;
2750  }
2751 
2752  Allocate = TRUE;
2753  Status = CmpCmdHiveOpen( SourceFile, // FileAttributes
2754  &ClientSecurityContext, // ImpersonationContext
2755  &Allocate, // Allocate
2756  &NewHive, // NewHive
2757  CM_CHECK_REGISTRY_CHECK_CLEAN // CheckFlags
2758  );
2759 
2760  SeDeleteClientSecurity( &ClientSecurityContext );
2761 
2762 
2763  if (!NT_SUCCESS(Status)) {
2764  if( KeyHandle != NULL ) {
2765  PCMHIVE LoadedHive = NULL;
2766 
2767  CmpLockRegistryExclusive();
2768 
2769  //
2770  // check if the same file is loaded in the same spot
2771  //
2772  if( CmpIsHiveAlreadyLoaded(KeyHandle,SourceFile,&LoadedHive) ) {
2773  ASSERT( LoadedHive );
2774  if( OtherHive != NULL ) {
2775  //
2776  // unjoin the existing class (if any) and join the new one
2777  //
2778  CmpUnJoinClassOfTrust(LoadedHive);
2779  CmpJoinClassOfTrust(LoadedHive,OtherHive);
2780  LoadedHive->Flags |= CM_CMHIVE_FLAG_UNTRUSTED;
2781  }
2782  Status = STATUS_SUCCESS;
2783  }
2784  CmpUnlockRegistry();
2785  }
2786 
2787  if( KeyHandle != NULL ) {
2788  ZwClose(KeyHandle);
2789  }
2790  return(Status);
2791  } else {
2792  //
2793  // we only need shared
2794  //
2795  CmpLockRegistry();
2796  }
2797 
2798  //
2799  // only one hive loading at a time (I can imagine getting rid of that, if needed)
2800  //
2801  LOCK_HIVE_LOAD();
2802  //
2803  // only this thread is allowed to use this hive for now.
2804  //
2805  NewHive->Hive.HiveFlags |= HIVE_IS_UNLOADING;
2806  NewHive->CreatorOwner = KeGetCurrentThread();
2807  //
2808  // if this is a NO_LAZY_FLUSH hive, set the appropriate bit.
2809  //
2810  if (Flags & REG_NO_LAZY_FLUSH) {
2811  NewHive->Hive.HiveFlags |= HIVE_NOLAZYFLUSH;
2812  }
2813  //
2814  // mark the hive as untrusted
2815  //
2816  NewHive->Flags |= CM_CMHIVE_FLAG_UNTRUSTED;
2817  if( OtherHive != NULL ) {
2818  //
2819  // join the same class of trust with the otherhive
2820  //
2821  CmpJoinClassOfTrust(NewHive,OtherHive);
2822  }
2823  //
2824  // We now have a succesfully loaded and initialized CmHive, so we
2825  // just need to link that into the appropriate spot in the master hive.
2826  //
2827  Status = CmpLinkHiveToMaster(TargetKey->ObjectName,
2828  TargetKey->RootDirectory,
2829  NewHive,
2830  Allocate,
2831  TargetKey->SecurityDescriptor);
2832 
2833  if (NT_SUCCESS(Status)) {
2834  //
2835  // add new hive to hivelist
2836  //
2837  CmpAddToHiveFileList(NewHive);
2838  //
2839  // flush the hive right here if just created; this is to avoid situations where
2840  // the lazy flusher doesn't get a chance to flush the hive, or it can't (because
2841  // the hive is a no_lazy_flush hive and it is never explicitly flushed)
2842  //
2843  if( Allocate == TRUE ) {
2844  CmpLockHiveFlusherExclusive(NewHive);
2845  HvSyncHive(&(NewHive->Hive));
2846  CmpUnlockHiveFlusher(NewHive);
2847  }
2848  //
2849  // allow others to use this hive
2850  //
2851  NewHive->Hive.HiveFlags &= (~HIVE_IS_UNLOADING);
2852  NewHive->CreatorOwner = NULL;
2853  UNLOCK_HIVE_LOAD();
2854 
2855  } else {
2856  LogHiveLoad((PHHIVE)NewHive,Status);
2857 
2858  CmpLockHiveListExclusive();
2859  CmpRemoveEntryList(&(NewHive->HiveList));
2860  CmpUnlockHiveList();
2861 
2862  UNLOCK_HIVE_LOAD();
2863 #if DBG
2864  NewHive->HiveIsLoading = TRUE;
2865 #endif
2866  CmpDestroyHiveViewList(NewHive);
2867  CmpDestroySecurityCache (NewHive);
2868  CmpDropFileObjectForHive(NewHive);
2869  CmpUnJoinClassOfTrust(NewHive);
2870 
2871  HvFreeHive((PHHIVE)NewHive);
2872 
2873  //
2874  // Close the hive files
2875  //
2876  CmpCmdHiveClose(NewHive);
2877 
2878  //
2879  // free the cm level structure
2880  //
2881  CmpFreeMutex(NewHive->ViewLock);
2882 #if DBG
2883  CmpFreeResource(NewHive->FlusherLock);
2884 #endif
2885  CmpFree(NewHive, sizeof(CMHIVE));
2886  }
2887 
2888  //
2889  // We've given user chance to log on, so turn on quota
2890  //
2891  if ((CmpProfileLoaded == FALSE) &&
2892  (CmpWasSetupBoot == FALSE)) {
2893  CmpProfileLoaded = TRUE;
2894  CmpSetGlobalQuotaAllowed();
2895  }
2896 
2897  CmpUnlockRegistry();
2898 
2899  if( KeyHandle != NULL ) {
2900  ZwClose(KeyHandle);
2901  }
2902  return(Status);
2903 }

2929 NTSTATUS
2930 CmUnloadKey(
2931  IN PCM_KEY_CONTROL_BLOCK Kcb,
2932  IN ULONG Flags,
2933  IN ULONG ControlFlags
2934  )
2935 
2936 /*++
2937 
2938 Routine Description:
2939 
2940  Unlinks a hive from its location in the registry, closes its file
2941  handles, and deallocates all its memory.
2942 
2943  There must be no key control blocks currently referencing the hive
2944  to be unloaded.
2945 
2946 Arguments:
2947 
2948  Hive - Supplies a pointer to the hive control structure for the
2949  hive to be unloaded
2950 
2951  Kcb - Supplies the key control block
2952 
2953  Flags - REG_FORCE_UNLOAD will first mark open handles as invalid
2954  and then unload the hive.
2955 
2956  KcbLocked - tells if the kcb is locked ex on entry
2957 
2958 Return Value:
2959 
2960  NTSTATUS
2961 
2962 --*/
2963 
2964 {
2965  PCMHIVE CmHive;
2966  LOGICAL Success;
2967  PHHIVE Hive;
2968  HCELL_INDEX Cell;
2969  UNICODE_STRING EntryName = {0};
2970  BOOLEAN Remove = FALSE;
2971  BOOLEAN KcbLocked = (ControlFlags & CM_UNLOAD_KCB_LOCKED)?TRUE:FALSE;
2972  BOOLEAN RegLockedEx = (ControlFlags & CM_UNLOAD_REG_LOCKED_EX)?TRUE:FALSE;
2973 
2974 
2975  CmKdPrintEx((DPFLTR_CONFIG_ID,CML_CM,"CmUnloadKey\n"));
2976 
2977  // sanity
2978  ASSERT( (KcbLocked && CmpIsKCBLockedExclusive(Kcb) && CmpIsKCBLockedExclusive(Kcb->ParentKcb)) || (CmpTestRegistryLockExclusive() == TRUE) );
2979

2981  Cell = Kcb->KeyCell;
2982  //
2983  // Make sure the cell passed in is the root cell of the hive.

3653  // cannot map view
3654  //
3655  return STATUS_INSUFFICIENT_RESOURCES;
3656  }
3657 
3658  // release the cell right here, as the registry is locked exclusively, so we don't care
3659  HvReleaseCell(Hive, Node->Parent);

3665  //

3676  return GetExceptionCode();
3677  }

3681  // the name.
3682

3685  //

3687  return STATUS_NO_LOG_SPACE;

3691  // mark the index dirty as we are going to free it on success
3692  //

3698  //

3700  return STATUS_NO_LOG_SPACE;

3704  if( (OldSubKeyList == HCELL_NIL) || (!HvMarkCellDirty(Hive, OldSubKeyList,FALSE)) ) {

3706  }

3708  if( Index == NULL ) {
3709  //
3710  // we just marked this dirty
3711  //
3712  ASSERT( FALSE );
3713  return STATUS_INSUFFICIENT_RESOURCES;
3714  }
3715  // release the cell right here, as the registry is locked exclusively, so we don't care
3716  HvReleaseCell(Hive, OldSubKeyList);
3717

3719  // mark all the index cells dirty
3720  //
3721  if( Index->Signature == CM_KEY_INDEX_ROOT ) {
3722  //
3723  // it's a root
3724  //

3726  // common sense
3727  ASSERT( (Index->List[i] != 0) && (Index->List[i] != HCELL_NIL) );
3728  if(!HvMarkCellDirty(Hive, Index->List[i],FALSE)) {
3729  return STATUS_NO_LOG_SPACE;
3730  }
3731  }
3732

3737  Hive,
3738  NodeSize,
3739  StorageType,
3740  Cell // in the same vicinity
3741  );

3744  }

3747  if( NewKeyNode == NULL ) {

3751  //
3752  ASSERT( FALSE );
3753  Status = STATUS_INSUFFICIENT_RESOURCES;
3754  goto ErrorExit;
3755  }

3757  HvReleaseCell(Hive, NewKeyCell);

3761  //

3767  NewKeyNode->Name,
3768  &NewKeyName);

3773  } else {

3775  }

3779  goto ErrorExit;
3780  }

3782  KeQuerySystemTime(&TimeStamp);

3787  //

3791  //
3792  ParentNode->SubKeyLists[StorageType] = CmpDuplicateIndex(Hive,OldSubKeyList,StorageType);
3793  if( ParentNode->SubKeyLists[StorageType] == HCELL_NIL ) {
3794  Status = STATUS_INSUFFICIENT_RESOURCES;
3795  goto ErrorExit;

3806  goto ErrorExit;
3807  }
3808

3811  //
3812  if( !CmpRemoveSubKey(Hive,Node->Parent,Cell) ) {
3813  Status = STATUS_INSUFFICIENT_RESOURCES;
3814  goto ErrorExit;
3815  }

3819  // will eventually get rehashed
3820  //
3821  OldNcb = KeyControlBlock->NameBlock;
3822  try {
3823  KeyControlBlock->NameBlock = CmpGetNameControlBlock (&NewKeyName,&NameUpCase);
3824  } except (EXCEPTION_EXECUTE_HANDLER) {
3825  CmKdPrintEx((DPFLTR_CONFIG_ID,CML_EXCEPTION,"!!CmRenameKey: code:%08lx\n", GetExceptionCode()));
3826  Status = GetExceptionCode();
3827  goto ErrorExit;
3828  }

3837  //
3838  if( !CmpUpdateParentForEachSon(Hive,NewKeyCell) ) {
3839  Status = STATUS_INSUFFICIENT_RESOURCES;
3840  goto ErrorExit;
3841  }
3842

3844  // 6. At this point we have it all done. We just need to free the old index and key_cell
3845  //
3846 
3847  //
3848  // free old index
3849  //
3850  Index = (PCM_KEY_INDEX)HvGetCell(Hive,OldSubKeyList);
3851  if( Index == NULL ) {
3852  //
3853  // we just marked this dirty
3854  //
3855  ASSERT( FALSE );
3856  Status = STATUS_INSUFFICIENT_RESOURCES;
3857  goto ErrorExit;
3858  }

3860  HvReleaseCell(Hive, OldSubKeyList);
3861

3864  // it's a root
3865  //

3868  ASSERT( (Index->List[i] != 0) && (Index->List[i] != HCELL_NIL) );
3869  HvFreeCell(Hive, Index->List[i]);
3870  }

3872  } else {

3875  //

3877  (Index->Signature == CM_KEY_FAST_LEAF) ||
3878  (Index->Signature == CM_KEY_HASH_LEAF)

3885  // free old cell
3886  //

3891  //

3902  KeyControlBlock->ParentKcb->KcbMaxNameLen = (USHORT)NameLength;

3907  //

3909  if( ConvKey != KeyControlBlock->ConvKey ) {

3912  // again with th new ConvKey
3913  //
3914  CmpRemoveKeyHash(&(KeyControlBlock->KeyHash));
3915  KeyControlBlock->ConvKey = ConvKey;
3916  CmpInsertKeyHash(&(KeyControlBlock->KeyHash),FALSE);
3917  }

3921  //

3923 
3924  //

3926  //
3927  ASSERT( OldNcb != NULL );

3940  }
3941 #endif
3942 
3943  return STATUS_SUCCESS;
3944 
3945 ErrorExit:
3946  if( OldSubKeyList != HCELL_NIL ) {
3947  //
3948  // we have attempted (maybe even succeeded) to duplicate parent's index)
3949  //
3950  if( ParentNode->SubKeyLists[StorageType] != HCELL_NIL ) {
3951  //
3952  // we need to free this as it is a duplicate
3953  //
3954  Index = (PCM_KEY_INDEX)HvGetCell(Hive,ParentNode->SubKeyLists[StorageType]);
3955  if( Index == NULL ) {
3956  //
3957  // could not map view;this shouldn't happen as we just allocated this cell
3958  //
3959  ASSERT( FALSE );
3960  } else {
3961  // release the cell right here, as the registry is locked exclusively, so we don't care
3962  HvReleaseCell(Hive, ParentNode->SubKeyLists[StorageType]);
3963 
3964  if( Index->Signature == CM_KEY_INDEX_ROOT ) {
3965  //
3966  // it's a root
3967  //
3968  for(i=0;i<Index->Count;i++) {
3969  // common sense
3970  ASSERT( (Index->List[i] != 0) && (Index->List[i] != HCELL_NIL) );
3971  HvFreeCell(Hive, Index->List[i]);
3972  }
3973 
3974  } else {
3975  //
3976  // should be a leaf
3977  //
3978  ASSERT((Index->Signature == CM_KEY_INDEX_LEAF) ||
3979  (Index->Signature == CM_KEY_FAST_LEAF) ||
3980  (Index->Signature == CM_KEY_HASH_LEAF)
3981  );
3982  ASSERT(Index->Count != 0);
3983  }
3984  HvFreeCell(Hive, ParentNode->SubKeyLists[StorageType]);
3985  }
3986 
3987  }
3988  //
3989  // restore the parent's index
3990  //
3991  ParentNode->SubKeyLists[StorageType] = OldSubKeyList;
3992  }
3993  ASSERT( NewKeyCell != HCELL_NIL );
3994  HvFreeCell(Hive,NewKeyCell);
3995 
3996  if( OldNcb != NULL ) {
3997  KeyControlBlock->NameBlock = OldNcb;
3998  }
3999 
4000  return Status;
4001 }

4003 NTSTATUS
4004 CmMoveKey(
4005  IN PCM_KEY_CONTROL_BLOCK KeyControlBlock
4006  )
4007 /*++
4008 
4009 Routine Description:
4010 
4011  Moves all the cells related to this kcb above the specified fileoffset.
4012 
4013  What needs to be done:
4014 
4015  1. mark all data that we are going to touch dirty
4016  2. Duplicate the key_node (and values and all cells involved)
4017  3. Update the parent for all children
4018  4. replace the new Key_cell in the parent's subkeylist
4019  5. Update the kcb and the kcb cache
4020  6. remove old subkey
4021 
4022 WARNING:
4023  after 3 we cannot fail anymore. if we do, we'll leak cells.
4024 
4025 Arguments:
4026 
4027  KeyControlBlock - pointer to kcb for key to operate on
4028 
4029 Return Value:
4030 
4031  NTSTATUS
4032 
4033 --*/
4034 {
4035  NTSTATUS Status;
4036  PHHIVE Hive;
4037  HCELL_INDEX OldKeyCell;
4038  HCELL_INDEX NewKeyCell = HCELL_NIL;
4039  HCELL_INDEX ParentKeyCell;
4040  HSTORAGE_TYPE StorageType;
4041  PCM_KEY_NODE OldKeyNode;
4042  PCM_KEY_NODE ParentKeyNode;
4043  PCM_KEY_NODE NewKeyNode;
4044  PCM_KEY_INDEX ParentIndex;
4045  PCM_KEY_INDEX OldIndex;
4046  ULONG i,j;
4047  HCELL_INDEX LeafCell;
4048  PCM_KEY_INDEX Leaf;
4049  PCM_KEY_FAST_INDEX FastIndex;
4050  PHCELL_INDEX ParentIndexLocation = NULL;
4051 
4052  PAGED_CODE();
4053

4055 
4056  ASSERT_CM_LOCK_OWNED_EXCLUSIVE();
4057 
4058  //
4059  // no edits, on keys marked for deletion
4060  //
4061  if (KeyControlBlock->Delete) {
4062  return STATUS_KEY_DELETED;
4063  }
4064 
4065  //
4066  // see if the newName is not already a subkey of parentKcb
4067  //
4068  Hive = KeyControlBlock->KeyHive;
4069  OldKeyCell = KeyControlBlock->KeyCell;
4070  StorageType = HvGetCellType(OldKeyCell);
4071 
4072  if( StorageType != Stable ) {
4073  //
4074  // nop the volatiles
4075  //
4076  return STATUS_SUCCESS;
4077  }
4078 
4079  if( OldKeyCell == Hive->BaseBlock->RootCell ) {
4080  //
4081  // this works only for stable keys.
4082  //
4083  return STATUS_INVALID_PARAMETER;
4084  }
4085 
4086  //
4087  // 1. mark all data that we are going to touch dirty
4088  //
4089  // parent's index, as we will replace the key node cell in it

4091  //

4093  if( OldKeyNode == NULL ) {
4094  //
4095  // cannot map view
4096  //
4097  return STATUS_INSUFFICIENT_RESOURCES;
4098  }
4099 
4100  if (! CmpMarkKeyDirty(Hive, OldKeyCell
4101 #if DBG
4102  ,FALSE
4103 #endif //DBG
4104  )) {
4105  HvReleaseCell(Hive, OldKeyCell);
4106  return STATUS_NO_LOG_SPACE;
4107  }
4108  // release the cell right here, as the registry is locked exclusively, and the key_cell is marked as dirty
4109  HvReleaseCell(Hive, OldKeyCell);
4110 
4111  if( OldKeyNode->Flags & KEY_SYM_LINK ) {
4112  //
4113  // we do not compact links
4114  //
4115  return STATUS_INVALID_PARAMETER;
4116  }
4117  if( OldKeyNode->SubKeyLists[Stable] != HCELL_NIL ) {
4118  //
4119  // mark the index dirty
4120  //
4121  OldIndex = (PCM_KEY_INDEX)HvGetCell(Hive, OldKeyNode->SubKeyLists[Stable]);
4122  if( OldIndex == NULL ) {
4123  //
4124  // we couldn't map the bin containing this cell
4125  //
4126  return STATUS_INSUFFICIENT_RESOURCES;
4127  }
4128  HvReleaseCell(Hive, OldKeyNode->SubKeyLists[Stable]);
4129  if( !HvMarkCellDirty(Hive, OldKeyNode->SubKeyLists[Stable],FALSE) ) {

4131  }
4132 
4133  if(OldIndex->Signature == CM_KEY_INDEX_ROOT) {
4134  for (i = 0; i < OldIndex->Count; i++) {
4135  if( !HvMarkCellDirty(Hive, OldIndex->List[i],FALSE) ) {
4136  return STATUS_NO_LOG_SPACE;

4138  }
4139  }
4140  }

4143  //
4144  // now in the parent's spot

4169

4171

4194  //

4200  }
4201  }
4202  if( ParentIndexLocation != NULL ) {

4204  }

4208  //
4209  // found it! remember the locations we want to update later and break the loop

4212  return STATUS_NO_LOG_SPACE;

4216  }
4217  }

4219  break;
4220  }
4221  }
4222  }
4223  } else if ( (ParentIndex->Signature == CM_KEY_FAST_LEAF) ||
4224  (ParentIndex->Signature == CM_KEY_HASH_LEAF)
4225  ) {
4226  FastIndex = (PCM_KEY_FAST_INDEX)ParentIndex;
4227  for(j=0;j<FastIndex->Count;j++) {
4228  if( FastIndex->List[j].Cell == OldKeyCell ) {
4229  //
4230  // found it! remember the locations we want to update later and break the loop
4231  //
4232  if( !HvMarkCellDirty(Hive, ParentKeyNode->SubKeyLists[Stable],FALSE) ) {
4233  return STATUS_NO_LOG_SPACE;
4234  }
4235  ParentIndexLocation = &(FastIndex->List[j].Cell);
4236  break;
4237  }
4238  }
4239  } else {
4240  for(j=0;j<ParentIndex->Count;j++) {
4241  if( ParentIndex->List[j] == OldKeyCell ) {
4242  //
4243  // found it! remember the locations we want to update later and break the loop
4244  //
4245  if( !HvMarkCellDirty(Hive, ParentKeyNode->SubKeyLists[Stable],FALSE) ) {
4246  return STATUS_NO_LOG_SPACE;
4247  }
4248  ParentIndexLocation = &(ParentIndex->List[j]);
4249  break;
4250  }
4251  }
4252  }
4253 
4254  // we should've find it !!!
4255  ASSERT( ParentIndexLocation != NULL );
4256 
4257  //
4258  // 2. Duplicate the key_node (and values and all cells involved)
4259  //
4260  Status = CmpDuplicateKey(Hive,OldKeyCell,&NewKeyCell);
4261  if( !NT_SUCCESS(Status) ) {

4263  }

4266  ASSERT( (NewKeyCell != HCELL_NIL) && (StorageType == (HSTORAGE_TYPE)HvGetCellType(NewKeyCell)));
4267

4270  //

4278  // From now on, WE CANNOT fails. we have everything marked dirty
4279  // we just update some fields. no resources required !
4280  // If we fail to free some cells, too bad, we'll leak some cells.
4281  //

4283
