4465 NTSTATUS
4466 CmCompressKey(
4467  IN PHHIVE Hive
4468  )
4469 /*++
4470 
4471 Routine Description:
4472 
4473  Compresses the kcb, by means of simulating an "in-place" SaveKey
4474 
4475  What needs to be done:
4476 
4477  1. iterate through the kcb tree and make a list of all the kcbs
4478  that need to be changed (their keycell will change during the process)
4479  2. iterate through the cache and compute an array of security cells.
4480  We'll need it to map security cells into the new hive.
4481  3. Save the hive into a temporary hive, preserving
4482  the volatile info in keynodes and updating the cell mappings.
4483  4. Update the cache by adding volatile security cells from the old hive.
4484  5. Dump temporary (compressed) hive over to the old file.
4485  6. Switch hive data from the compressed one to the existing one and update
4486  the kcb KeyCell and security mapping
4487  7. Invalidate the map and drop paged bins.
4488  8. Free storage for the new hive (OK if we fail)
4489 
4490 Arguments:
4491 
4492  Hive - Hive to operate on
4493 
4494 Return Value:
4495 
4496  NTSTATUS
4497 
4498 --*/
4499 {
4500  NTSTATUS Status = STATUS_SUCCESS;
4501  HCELL_INDEX KeyCell;
4502  PCMHIVE CmHive;
4503  PCM_KCB_REMAP_BLOCK RemapBlock;
4504  PCMHIVE NewHive = NULL;
4505  HCELL_INDEX LinkCell;
4506  PCM_KEY_NODE LinkNode;
4507  PCM_KNODE_REMAP_BLOCK KnodeRemapBlock;
4508  ULONG OldLength;
4509 
4510 
4511  PAGED_CODE();
4512 
4513  CmKdPrintEx((DPFLTR_CONFIG_ID,CML_CM,"CmCompressKey\n"));
4514 
4515  ASSERT_CM_LOCK_OWNED_EXCLUSIVE();
4516 
4517  if( HvAutoCompressCheck(Hive) == FALSE ) {
4518  return STATUS_SUCCESS;
4519  }
4520 
4521  KeyCell = Hive->BaseBlock->RootCell;
4522  CmHive = CONTAINING_RECORD(Hive, CMHIVE, Hive);
4523  //
4524  // Make sure the cell passed in is the root cell of the hive.
4525  //
4526  if ( CmHive == CmpMasterHive ) {
4527  return STATUS_INVALID_PARAMETER;
4528  }
4529 
4530  //
4531  // 0. Get the cells we need to relink the compressed hive
4532  //
4533  LinkNode = (PCM_KEY_NODE)HvGetCell(Hive,KeyCell);
4534  if( LinkNode == NULL ) {
4535  return STATUS_INSUFFICIENT_RESOURCES;
4536  }
4537  LinkCell = LinkNode->Parent;
4538  HvReleaseCell(Hive,KeyCell);
4539  LinkNode = (PCM_KEY_NODE)HvGetCell((PHHIVE)CmpMasterHive,LinkCell);
4540 
4541  // master storage is paged pool
4542  ASSERT(LinkNode != NULL);
4543  HvReleaseCell((PHHIVE)CmpMasterHive,LinkCell);
4544 
4545  OldLength = Hive->BaseBlock->Length;
4546 
4547  //
4548  // 1. iterate through the kcb tree and make a list of all the kcbs
4549  // that need to be changed (their keycell will change during the process)
4550  //
4551  ASSERT( IsListEmpty(&(CmHive->KcbConvertListHead)) );
4552 
4553  //
4554  // this will kick all kcb with refcount == 0 out of cache, so we can use
4555  // CmpSearchKeyControlBlockTree for recording referenced kcbs
4556  //
4557  CmpCleanUpKCBCacheTable(NULL,TRUE);
4558  if( !CmpSearchKeyControlBlockTree(CmpCompressKeyWorker,(PVOID)Hive,(PVOID)(&(CmHive->KcbConvertListHead))) ) {
4559  Status = STATUS_INSUFFICIENT_RESOURCES;
4560  goto Exit;
4561  }
4562 
4563  //
4564  // 2. iterate through the cache and compute an array of security cells.
4565  // We'll need it to map security cells into the new hive.
4566  //
4567  if( !CmpBuildSecurityCellMappingArray(CmHive) ) {
4568  Status = STATUS_INSUFFICIENT_RESOURCES;
4569  goto Exit;
4570  }
4571 
4572  //
4573  // 3. Save the hive into a temporary hive , preserving
4574  // the volatile info in keynodes and updating the cell mappings.
4575  //
4576  Status = CmpShiftHiveFreeBins(CmHive,&NewHive);
4577  if( !NT_SUCCESS(Status) ) {
4578  goto Exit;
4579  }
4580 
4581  //
4582  // 5. Dump temporary (compressed) hive over to the old file.
4583  //
4584  Status = CmpOverwriteHive(CmHive,NewHive,LinkCell);
4585  if (!NT_SUCCESS(Status)) {
4586  goto Exit;
4587  }
4588 
4589 
4590  //
4591  // From this point on, we WILL NOT FAIL!
4592  //
4593 
4594  //
4595  // get the root node and link it into the master storage
4596  //
4597  LinkNode->ChildHiveReference.KeyCell = NewHive->Hive.BaseBlock->RootCell;
4598 
4599  //
4600  // 6. Switch hive data from the compressed one to the existing one and update
4601  // the kcb KeyCell and security mapping
4602  // This should better NOT fail!!! If it does, we are doomed, as we have partial
4603  // data => bugcheck
4604  //
4605  CmpSwitchStorageAndRebuildMappings(CmHive,NewHive);
4606 
4607 
4608  //
4609  // 7. Invalidate the map and drop paged bins. If system hive, check for the hysteresis callback.
4610  //
4611  HvpDropAllPagedBins(&(CmHive->Hive));
4612  if( OldLength < CmHive->Hive.BaseBlock->Length ) {
4613  CmpUpdateSystemHiveHysteresis(&(CmHive->Hive),CmHive->Hive.BaseBlock->Length,OldLength);
4614  }
4615 
4616 
4617 Exit:
4618 
4619  //
4620  // 8. Free storage for the new hive (OK if we fail)
4621  //
4622  if( NewHive != NULL ) {
4623  CmpDestroyTemporaryHive(NewHive);
4624  }
4625 
4626  if( CmHive->CellRemapArray != NULL ) {
4627  ExFreePool(CmHive->CellRemapArray);
4628  CmHive->CellRemapArray = NULL;
4629  }
4630  //
4631  // remove all remap blocks and free them
4632  //
4633  while (IsListEmpty(&(CmHive->KcbConvertListHead)) == FALSE) {
4634  RemapBlock = (PCM_KCB_REMAP_BLOCK)RemoveHeadList(&(CmHive->KcbConvertListHead));
4635  RemapBlock = CONTAINING_RECORD(
4636  RemapBlock,
4637  CM_KCB_REMAP_BLOCK,
4638  RemapList
4639  );
4640  ExFreePool(RemapBlock);
4641  }
4642  while (IsListEmpty(&(CmHive->KnodeConvertListHead)) == FALSE) {
4643  KnodeRemapBlock = (PCM_KNODE_REMAP_BLOCK)RemoveHeadList(&(CmHive->KnodeConvertListHead));
4644  KnodeRemapBlock = CONTAINING_RECORD(
4645  KnodeRemapBlock,
4646  CM_KNODE_REMAP_BLOCK,
4647  RemapList
4648  );
4649  ExFreePool(KnodeRemapBlock);
4650  }
4651 
4652  return Status;
4653 }

4712  Most of the SetValue calls are noops (i.e. they are setting the same

4733  TRUE - same value with the same data exist in the cache.
4734 
4735 --*/

4749

4751

4753

4755  //

4757  //

4759  if( (CmpIsKCBLockedExclusive(KeyControlBlock) == FALSE) &&
4760  (CmpTryConvertKCBLockSharedToExclusive(KeyControlBlock) == FALSE) ) {
4761  //
4762  // need to upgrade lock to exclusive
4763  //
4764  return SearchNeedExclusiveLock;
4765  }
4766 
4767  Node = (PCM_KEY_NODE)HvGetCell(KeyControlBlock->KeyHive,KeyControlBlock->KeyCell);
4768 
4769  if( Node == NULL ) {
4770  //
4771  // we couldn't map the bin containing this cell
4772  //
4773  return SearchFail;
4774  }

4778 
4779  HvReleaseCell(KeyControlBlock->KeyHive,KeyControlBlock->KeyCell);

4804

4819  //

4824  } except (EXCEPTION_EXECUTE_HANDLER) {
4825  SearchValue = SearchFail;

4827  }
4828 
4829  } else {
4830  compareSize = 0;
4831  }
4832 
4833  if (compareSize != DataSize) {
4834  SearchValue = SearchFail;
4835  }
4836 
4837  } else {

4839  }

4841 
4842 Exit:

4844  if(ValueDataCellToRelease != HCELL_NIL) {
4845  HvReleaseCell(KeyControlBlock->KeyHive,ValueDataCellToRelease);
4846  }

4849  }
